title: chess cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Mix melted butter, 1 egg and cake mix; spread in buttered pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until cake rises and falls.
Cool before serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper;
add tomato sauce, tomato soup, 1/2 cup water, lemon juice and seasoning to
taste (salt and pepper).
Let simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Add
shrimp. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour cherry pie filling evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread crushed pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over nuts.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: brownie ice cream
directions: Pour dry brownie mix into long glass or metal baking dish. Cut up margarine into the dry mix.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Stir until margarine is completely mixed.
Bake 10 more minutes. Crumble mix to break into small pieces.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Can substitute strawberries and peaches with the same flavor of pie fillings. Also, may want to use 2 cans of oranges instead of 1.

title: pokey pudding
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat altogether until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Put Cool Whip around edges.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: grand traverse cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425° for 5 minutes.
Line pie pan with pie crust. Spread filling evenly in crust.

title: down home sausage and cheese pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of prepared pie crust with fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°. Sprinkle half of sausage over partially baked crust.
Combine remaining ingredients (except sausage) and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with remaining sausage.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: quick chicken jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Place in large baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: turkey skillet
directions: Brown turkey and onion.
Add salt, pepper and bouillon.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes are done.

title: cookies for birds
directions: Mix and knead Bisquick and water into a stiff dough.
If needed, add more Bisquick or flour.
Flatten, roll and cut out with a cookie cutter.
Pat "cookie" into bird seed.
Poke a hole with a straw for a hanger.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: crullers (french donuts)
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt, sugar and lemon rind.
Combine water and butter in saucepan.
Stir until butter melts, bringing to a boil.
Add flour mixture.
Cook and stir until batter leaves sides of pan and forms a ball around the spoon (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Chill.
Put through pastry tube or cookie press, using largest serrated tip to form circles on a greased pancake turner. Slip into deep fat heated to 375°.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Dip warm donuts into warm glaze.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: herber yogurt cheese
directions: Line a 6-inch strainer with coffee filter.
Place strainer over bowl.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into strainer. Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours. Unmold onto plate.
Garnish with pepper and dill weed.
Per tablespoon contains 25 calories and 0 gm fat.

title: apple butterscotch jam cake
directions: Blend cake and pudding mixes with water and oil.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in nuts and preserves. Bake in a 350° oven in well greased and floured tube pan for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Add salt, soda and baking powder and spice; sift again.
Add nuts.
Combine oil, pumpkin, sugar and eggs.
Beat well until blended and light; add dry ingredients. Pour into greased pan (10-inch tube or Bundt pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form small balls and flatten on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Dip chicken in a mixture of flour, nutmeg, white pepper and salt.
Saute and brown chicken.
Add mixture of cream of mushroom soup, champagne, white grapes and cook for 1 hour at 350°.	Serve topped with white grapes and scallions.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Brown meat in butter, salt, pepper, garlic salt, onions and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream with noodles. Alternate layers of noodles with mixture of meat, beginning with noodles and ending with meat.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted or browned.

title: belinda's mexican dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a dish, then mix the last 3 ingredients together.
Spread the cream cheese mixture in a shallow pan.
Put taco sauce on top of mixture, then place chopped veggies on top.
Top with shredded cheese (Monterey Jack or Cheddar).
Use plain nacho chips to dip.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually.
Beat again.
Add butter, potatoes and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Divide in half.
Chill 2 hours.
Take out 1/2 at a time. Roll on floured board, 1/2-inch thick; cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in oil until golden on both sides.
Dry on paper towels. While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cinnamon.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Pour batter into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool before removing.

title: candy apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Remove stems.
Insert skewers in apples. Combine sugar, syrup and water in heavy saucepan.
Mix well. Cook without stirring to 285° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add red food coloring.
Hold each apple by skewers and quickly twirl in syrup; allow excess to drip off.
Put on lightly buttered pan.

title: down-home chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, whisk together cocoa and boiling water until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Whisk in vanilla and mayonnaise.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix on low speed for 30 seconds.
Add chocolate mixture and mix on low speed until moist.
Increase to medium speed and beat for 1 minute.
Scrape batter into two prepared pans and fill only 1/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Allow cake to cool for 10 minutes.
Invert onto greased tacks.
Cool completely.

title: salted peanut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg and egg yolks to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix or blend well. Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red flannel hash
directions: The amounts given are intended to show proportions rather than actual amounts, since leftovers seldom come out evenly.
The rule of thumb is to have equal amounts of corned beef and potatoes and enough beets to make the hash dark red.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Slice tomatoes and vegetables.
Add cloves.
Boil until soft. Put through fruit press.
Add to juice the salt, sugar and lemon juice or vinegar.

title: tea punch
directions: If sugar is used, place in a 1-gallon container.
While tea is still hot, pour over sugar and mix well.
Add juices and mix. Fill container with enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, salt, garlic and cloves.
Stir in water and vinegar slowly.
Blend thoroughly and pour over beets and onion.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lentil soup(high protein, low cholesterol)
directions: Wash lentils and bring to a slow boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, another 30 minutes to an hour.
Excellent served with corn bread. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: parsley buttered carrots
directions: Place butter or margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in oven for 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Add mandarin oranges, salt and ginger.

title: bavarian supper sandwich
directions: Slowly fry sausage until done.
Remove sausage; reserve 2 teaspoons fat.
Cook onions in reserved fat until tender, but not brown.
Combine biscuit mix, poppy seed, milk and egg; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with sausage, then onions.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place onion and butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook in microwave on full power for 1 1/2 minutes or until onion is tender.
Blend in flour, seasonings, water and bouillon.
Cook in microwave on full power for 4 minutes or until thickened.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Add potatoes.
Stir lightly to coat.
Cook in microwave, covered, on full power for 13 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese as desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: home stack cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
You may add extra flour to thicken if you like.
In a greased and floured cake pan, pour a very thin layer.
Bake until golden brown at 350°, usually about 15 minutes.
(Oven times may vary.)

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in saucepan.
Add onion, garlic and chili powder.
Cook, stirring, until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until thickened (30 minutes).

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In pie plate, dip chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs.
In skillet, over medium-low heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove and keep warm.

title: orange refrigerator cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
In large bowl combine shortening, butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and egg.
Beat one minute.
Add orange juice, orange rind, lemon extract and pecans.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until blended.
Shape into rolls; chill.
Slice and put on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Can freeze.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Blend all items in blender, starting with cheese, then vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and oil from salmon.
Add all other ingredients.
Dip may be thinned with water or more mayonnaise. Serve either as dip or spread.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Add noodles.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let set until firm.

title: old fashioned bran muffins
directions: Combine All-Bran and milk.
Let stand until most of the moisture is taken up. Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add to first mixture, stirring only until combined. Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 9 muffins.

title: cream cheese ham balls
directions: Blend ingredients thoroughly, except chives, and form into tiny balls.
Roll in chopped chives.
Serve speared on toothpicks. Makes about 30 balls.

title: easy banana pound cake
directions: Mix bananas, oil and sugar well. Add cake mix to this and beat with electric mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla and pecans. Spray Bundt pan with Pam and pour mixture in. Will also make 2 loaf size pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the sausage, Bisquick and Cheddar cheese together using your hands to mix.
The moisture in the sausage and cheese will hold the mixture together.
Roll into balls and bake for 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large skillet.
Mix shoyu sauce, wine, oil, ginger, garlic powder and brown sugar together; pour over chicken. Cook on medium heat; keep turning chicken parts over.
When all the broth is gone, put chicken on a cookie sheet and broil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown the bacon in a heavy skillet, remove bacon and turn down heat.
Pour beaten eggs in the skillet and scramble slightly. Add remaining ingredients and soy sauce to taste, stir to mix. Cook 15 minutes.
Add green peas the last 5 minutes, they just need to thaw out.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Heat to boiling and remove from the heat.
Cool.
Pour over sliced cukes, onion and pepper that have been mixed together in a large jar.
Keep in the refrigerator until used.
Will keep up to a year!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan mix sugar, cornstarch, flour, and salt. Gradually add hot water, stirring constantly. Cook and stir over high heat until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat, cook and stir 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat. Stir small amount of

hot mixture into egg yolks, then return to hot mixture. Bring to boiling and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add butter and lemon peel. Slowly add lemon juice, mixing well. Pour into shell or spoon into tart shells. Spread meringue over filling, seal to edge. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Melt all soups together.
Add chicken.
Line casserole dish with Doritos and pour melted mixture on top.
Add more Doritos on top.

title: quickies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Add quick oats.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not bake.
Let set up, then cut in squares.

title: five-hour oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix gently, but well. Turn into 3-quart casserole.
Cover with lid and bake at 275°
for 5 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple stacked cake
directions: Cake:
Use buttermilk and eggs to substitute ingredients on package.
Mix cake according to directions on cake package, pouring batter into 3 prepared pans.
Bake per package directions. Adjust time for 3 layers or you may bake just 2 layers.
Slice each layer in two, making 4 layers.

title: nacho layered dip
directions: Bottom Layer:
Spread bean dip in large rectangular pan.

title: marriage stew(two full servings)
directions: Take one grassy field, 1/2 dozen small children, 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well together and put them into the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles.
Sprinkle the field with flowers, spread over all a deep blue sky, and bake in a hot sun.
When brown, remove and set away to cool in a bathtub."

title: kahlua
directions: Boil 2 cups water with the sugar for 6 minutes.
Add vanilla. Mix instant coffee with 1 cup boiling water; gradually add to boiled sugar and water mixture.
Add vodka and glycerin.
Cool. Place into a dark bottle with a tight lid.
Let set at least 30 days.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix together for sandwiches.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat out cookie dough in pizza pan and cook until golden brown. Set aside and cool.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles until soft; drain.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon and raisins in a large bowl.
Add the noodles.
Heat glass baking dish with butter (small amount) in oven.
Remove and add mixture (9 x 13-inch or 8 x 8-inch pans). Bake in 350° oven until set.
Serves 10.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Spread over nuts and coconut.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese together.
Pour over cake mix in pan.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: crescent pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Separate dough into 2 large rectangles. Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up side of prepared pan.
Seal perforations.
Bake crust for 5 minutes.

title: honey barbecued broilers
directions: Combine butter or margarine, vinegar, honey, garlic, salt, mustard, marjoram and pepper; mix well.
Place chicken, skin side down, on grill.
Tuck wings under.
Broil over low coals for 20 minutes.
Generously brush broiled side of chicken with honey sauce; turn.
Broil 10 minutes.
Brush with sauce and turn.
Broil 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Just before serving, brush again with sauce.
Makes 6 servings.
Enough sauce for 10 to 12 breasts.
Very good!

title: rum cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, 1/2 cup rum, 1/2 cup water, oil and eggs in bowl.
Beat for exactly 2 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan sprinkled with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: cool carrots
directions: Combine soup, sugar and mustard; add vinegar and oil.
Mix well; add pepper and onion.
Pour over cooled carrots. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and butter.
Add lemon juice and peel.
Add to combined egg yolks and milk; mix well.
Fold in egg whites and pour into greased casserole or custard cups.
Bake in pan of hot water in moderate oven (325°) for 45 minutes.
Custard will be on bottom, sponge cake on top.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses together.
Add pimento, pepper and onion. Add Worcestershire, lemon juice, salt and cayenne.
Stir until smooth. Form into ball and chill.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; beat until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add honey, milk, flour, spices and baking powder. Beat until well mixed.
Add figs, raisins and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Do not overbake.

title: pineapple pecan cheese spread
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into decorative crock, jar or container.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.
Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: fiesta bowl chicken and wild rice casserole(may be prepared ahead and frozen)
directions: Wash chickens; place in large cooking kettle and add sherry, celery, onion, salt, curry powder and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Remove and set aside to cool.
Strain broth and measure it.
Cook rice using chicken broth for water called for on package (add water if necessary).

title: hamapple and cheese sandwich
directions: Combine ham, apple (drained), mayonnaise and mustard.
Lightly butter the bread.
Evenly spread ham mixture on 4 slices.
Add cheese and tomato slices and top with other slices of bread. Serves 4.

title: german white cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together until creamy, then add eggs one at a time.
Add the next 3 ingredients until all the flour is mixed in.
Add the last 3 ingredients and mix them in. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: In a large pan, cook chicken and tear into strips.
Add beans and broth.
In skillet, cook onions, peppers, garlic and spices. Add all ingredients together in large pan and simmer on low for 2 hours.
Serve with beer and watch ball game.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400. Mix chicken, vegetables, soup, salt and pepper together.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Wash and prepare chicken parts of your choice.
Brown or boil chicken.
Mix catsup and Pepsi or Coke (diet may be used) to medium thickness.
Simmer the cooked chicken in the sauce for about 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together pudding and cake mix, then add everything, except the poppy seed.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Fold in poppy seed.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: terry's jambalaya
directions: Skin snake and cut in 3 and 4-inch pieces.
Roll in mixture of flour, corn meal, milk and egg. Salt and pepper to taste. Deep fry in hot oil. Serve hot.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Cook green
beans
until crisp-tender.
Toss with vinegar, onion, salt,
garlic
and
pepper.
Pour
into casserole. Stir together crumbs,
cheese and butter; sprinkle over beans. (Can be prepared early
in
the
day,
except do not add crumb mixture.) Before baking,
stir beans, then add crumbs over the top, then place in oven
to
bake.
Bake
at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: delicious quick 'n easy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; when tender, drain.
Add rest of ingredients. Serve immediately or may be left on low heat to keep hot.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and pat butter, flour, nuts and sugar in buttered dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Mix and spread cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip over the 1st layer.
Beat milk and pudding until thick; pour over second layer.
Cover with Cool Whip, then sprinkle with nuts.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Slice the zucchini and onion.
Melt oleo or butter in frypan. Add zucchini and onion and saute until they are transparent.
(Do not brown.)
When cooked, add chicken broth. Salt and pepper.
Put in blender and puree.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix jello powder and boiling water as directed on package.
Add cold water.
Place angel food cake in large bowl big enough to cover cake.
Pour jello over top of cake.
Weight cake down by placing cookie sheet on top and setting heavy object on to keep cake under jello.
Chill in refrigerator 4 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix sour cream and soup mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.
Serve. Great for vegetables, on potatoes or with chips.

title: buffet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Boil tomatoes and sugar 10 minutes until foam off.
Add Jell-O. Stir well and pour in jars.
Can use red tomatoes and lemon Jell-O.

title: chocolate chip coconut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, butter, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: icy lemonade
directions: Place half of the lemonade concentrate and 12 - 15 ice cubes in blender, add 2 cups of soda.
Cover and process on high until ice is crushed.
Repeat.
Serve immediately.

title: tex-mex chip dip
directions: Shred cheese.
Mix together the Uncle Dan's seasoning mix and sour cream.
Take a shallow baking dish and put refried beans (layer), sour cream and seasoning mix (layer), olives (layer), avocados (layer) and Cheddar cheese (layer).
Continue until all ingredients are gone.
Use corn chips for dipping.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon of the oil into a large skillet.
Preheat over medium heat.
Add eggs.
Lift and tilt the skillet to form a thin sheet of egg.
Cook, without stirring, about 2 minutes or just until set.
Slide sheet onto a cutting board.
Cut into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy blue cheese dip
directions: Beat together Blue cheese and cream cheese until smooth.
Add tomato juice and horseradish.
Cover and chill to blend flavors. Use as dip with vegetables or filling for celery.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package instructions.
Cut chicken into cube size pieces.
Stir-fry chicken until done.
In a separate dish, you can heat the cream of chicken soup so it will already be warm.
Once chicken is cooked, soup is cooked and stuffing is done, combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place in oven at 325° for about 20 minutes.
tags: Stove Top stuffing mix for chicken

title: cheese and bacon franks
directions: Combine cheese, butter and mustard.
Split frankfurters almost through.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Split rolls.
Spread with butter.
Place frankfurters in rolls.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Tuck pickle and bacon in rolls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pasta with broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Saute garlic, then pepper and broccoli.
Cover, let simmer briefly.
Add mushrooms, water and wine.
Add butter.
Cook and drain pasta.
Toss with butter.
Spoon vegetables on top.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in bottom of well-greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls. Melt together margarine and brown sugar. Add pecans. Pour over rolls and pudding. Cover tightly with foil. Leave overnight. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Let stand about 20 minutes before turning out onto plate.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown meat with onion and peppers.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, 1 cup corn and milk with cornbread mix. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with beef mixture, cheese slices and remaining 1 cup corn.
Pour remaining half of batter on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Line bottom of bowl with a layer of shortcake, pound cake or ladyfingers.
Pour drained fruit cocktail over cake.
Prepare jello as directed, pour over fruit and cake mixture and refrigerate until set.
Prepare instant vanilla pudding and pour over jello.
Top with your favorite whipped cream.

title: basil carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water for 20 to 22 minutes.
Drain. Melt margarine and then add other ingredients.
Add carrots and toss.

title: maple nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil, add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well, add nuts and maple flavoring. Pour into 9x13 baking pan.
Top with powdered sugar. Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a bowl; add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream, mayo and taco mix.
Spread two 10 1/2 ounce cans plain or jalapeno flavored bean dip or a large 13 ounce can of refried beans in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with mixture; sprinkle with 1 large bunch of chopped green onions (1 cup). Next, cover with sliced ripe olives, then 1 package (8 ounces) sharp Cheddar cheese, grated.
Serve chilled or room temperature with round tortillas.

title: pineapple-orange sunshine cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 33 to 37 minutes in two 8-inch baking pans.
3.6 grams fat.

title: corn bread old fashioned
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with milk.
Add eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Either cook on top of stove or bake in the oven at 350°.
Bake until corn bread is brown.

title: corn dish
directions: In a large pan melt the butter and the cream cheese.
Drain the first 3 kinds of corn.
Add all of the corn to the butter and cream cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together sugar and shortening.
Stir in egg and pumpkin. In second bowl, sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Blend in with creamed mixture. Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: You will need an electric skillet.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place a crust in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix ingredients together adding pecans last.
Pour into shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until set.
If nuts are salted, omit salt from filling.

title: squash bake
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough buttermilk to make mixture very mushy.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and horseradish for about 10 minutes at high speed until consistency of whipped cream.
Fold in crab meat.
Bake in buttered dish for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix together.
Put half in large pan.
Put in 200° oven for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 5 minutes.
Then do the same to the other half.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, beat eggs. Add oleo and bananas.
Combine all together, then pecans last. Bake at 350° until done, 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen and eaten at a later time.

title: bagel pizza bites
directions: Place half a bagel on cookie sheet.
Spoon on sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top and place pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
I use Baker's Joy to prepare cake pan.
In a large bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add wafer crumbs alternately with milk.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour in prepared tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: "philly" 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Top with blueberry topping. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with wire wisk until smooth.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and candy.
Freeze until firm or about 6 hours.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Cut brown paper to
fit
bottom
of
two
medium cookie sheets.
Turn oven on at
Beat
egg whites until stiff; add sugar and salt.
Add
vanilla and beat until well blended. Fold in the chocolate chips
and
pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on the brown paper and place in the preheated oven.
Cut the oven off and leave in the oven for at least 2 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in skillet, add brown sugar and dissolve.
Place pineapple slice on mixture and set aside.
Beat egg yolks and add sugar and pineapple juice.
Mix and add flour and baking powder sifted together.
Beat and fold in egg whites that have been stiffly beaten.
Pour batter into skillet and bake at 350° until cake is brownish.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onions in margarine until clear.
Add the other ingredients together.
Cook at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat together powdered sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat these ingredients for 20 minutes.
Pour the mix over the graham crust. Slice bananas and place over the cream filling.
Drain a large can of pineapple and add pineapple only to cake.
Spread a large carton of Cool Whip on the top of bananas and pineapple, then garnish with pecans and cherries to make it look pretty.

title: nutty fruit conserve
directions: In a large pot, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 20 minutes, adding the almonds during the last 5 minutes.
Quickly stir in pectin. Bring to a full rolling boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Skim off any foam.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles. Adjust caps.
Process for 15 minutes in a boiling water bath. Yields 5 pints.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir until jello is dissolved.
Combine water and ice cubes and add to jello.
Stir until ice melts.
Fold in strawberries and Cool Whip.
Pour over angel food cake that you have torn into small pieces in a bowl. Refrigerate until set.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Shape into whatever size meatballs you like. Brown in electric skillet with 3 tablespoons of olive oil. Brown on all sides. Serve with your own sauce.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and make up as regular biscuits or you can mix with spoon and add a little more liquid to make a sticky, stiff dough.
Cover and refrigerate; use as desired.
Cut out with a spoon.
Roll out very thin and place on greased pan.
Put butter on top of each one and bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Refreeze.
Let sit a few minutes before cutting and serving.

title: chili pie
directions: In a casserole dish, place in layers: crushed corn chips on bottom, then chili with cheese following; layer these until ingredients are used.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix peanut butter, shortening, sugar, water and Bisquick.
Roll into balls.
Put on cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bob's seafood stuffing
directions: Chop onion; chop crab meat and shrimp.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.

title: corn oysters
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in a medium bowl until well blended.
Heat half the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Drop 6 heaping tablespoons corn mixture into skillet.
Cook 2 minutes; turn with a spatula and cook 2 minutes more until lightly brown.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Serves 4.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Thaw frozen hash browns a little.
Mix the rest of the ingredients with the potatoes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: grapefruit cole slaw
directions: Chill grapefruit. Cut off peel from top to bottom, slicing deep enough to remove white membrane.
Place sections in bowl with cabbage.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to cabbage.
Toss lightly.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
In another bowl, combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Pour strawberry mixture into dry mixture and mix well.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given: salmon, oleo, bread crumbs, hot milk,
eggs, salt and pepper.
Press into buttered bread pan.	Bake 30
minutes
in oven at 375°.
Serve with egg sauce, if desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sugars, eggs, one stick margarine and potatoes. Mix crumbs, remaining margarine
and nuts.
Put potato mixture in greased casserole.	Top with crumb mixture and bake in 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stir-fry beef and broccoli
directions: Brown stew meat in hot oil in wok on all sides.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Cook onion in oil until tender.
Remove and add to beef.
Set aside.
Add broccoli and stir-fry until broccoli partially tender.
Combine broth, soy sauce and cornstarch in small bowl.
Add reserved beef and onion to broccoli.
Pour broth mixture over all.
Stir to mix.
Lower heat to simmer and simmer for 5 minutes, covered.
Add tomato wedges and gently mix with other ingredients.
Cook until tomatoes and just heated through.
Serve on bed of rice.

title: pork with straw mushrooms
directions: Marinate pork for 20 minutes or overnight in refrigerator using soy sauce, white wine, egg white, sesame seed oil, cornstarch and pepper.
Thaw and hold mushrooms and corn.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add all remaining ingredients except flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour (one cup at a time). Roll on a floured board.
Dough will be a little hard to work with at first, but it will get firmer as you re-roll.
Cut with glass or cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookie bottoms begin to turn brown.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: macaroni
directions: In a bowl, mix cheese, pimentos, onion, butter, soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni and drain.
(Don't fully cook macaroni.)
Mix in macaroni and put in a greased dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown at 400°.

title: don's honey french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a quart jar and chill.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and cream.
Put soda into buttermilk and add alternately with flour.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan and fill with batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: manicotti
directions: Fry the hamburger until brown.
Drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer.
Boil shells for about 10 minutes.
Mix all three cheeses.
Drain water off shells; fill with cheese sauce. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour hamburger sauce over the shells.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute chopped onions in a small amount of olive oil.
Add thyme and chicken stock.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add cream and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Puree until smooth.
Season with salt and white pepper.
Garnish with onion slices.

title: valenti's pasta
directions: In a large frying pan, saute garlic in olive oil.
Add mushrooms, salt and red pepper.
Saute until mushrooms are tender. In a large pot, boil broccoli about 3 minutes.
Add peas and boil another 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables with a slotted spoon and add to mushroom mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In the vegetable water, boil pasta until done.
Drain and toss with butter and cheese. Pour the vegetables over the pasta and mix.
Top with more cheese. Mangia!

title: rolled fillet of fish
directions: Roll 1 piece of fish with 1 asparagus spear; pin with a toothpick and put 1/4 piece of tomato on toothpick.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice on top and pour 1/2 cup of water on top. Put on aluminum foil and cover top with foil on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: granola cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine; add oil, then sugars, egg, flour, vanilla, cereal, and nuts.
After all is well stirred, take a teaspoonful or tablespoonful and roll into ball.
Press on a cookie sheet sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Cook 12 minutes for light cookie, 15 to 18 minutes for darker, crunchier cookies.
You can also refrigerate these in wax paper sprayed with no-stick cooking spray, then slice and bake.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat the peanut butter and oleo in the microwave on high for 4 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 200° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix the applesauce and baking soda together in separate bowls. Cream shortening and sugar together.
Blend in applesauce and baking soda mixture.
Stir in raisins, then dry ingredients and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
In a blender, process bananas, pineapple and juices until smooth.
In a large container, mix the banana-pineapple mixture and the sugar water. Freeze.
When ready to use, let thaw about 1 hour or more.
Place in a punch bowl and add the 7-Up.
Stir and break into large pieces to make a slush.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and egg.
Mix well.
Add sugar; stir in oil. Combine remaining ingredients and add.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Batter will be thick.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add butter and vanilla last.
Great served warm over yellow cake. Makes about 2 1/2 cups sauce.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In 13 x 8-inch pan, layer 6 trimmed slices of bread.
Brown sausage or ham and drain.
Cover with cheese slices (add extra grated cheese if you like lots of cheese).
Cover with 6 more trimmed slices of bread.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over casserole.
Melt margarine and pour over eggs.
Top with bread crumbs or Ritz crackers or crumbled cereal.
Make the night before. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: country apple muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add chopped apples and stir to coat with flour mixture.
In a small bowl, beat together milk, oil and eggs. Add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in pot with water (enough to cover).
Add 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
After eggs are boiled, drain and cover with cold water.
When cool, drain and peel.
Cut eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
In small bowl, mash yolks with a fork.
Mix in 1 tablespoon vinegar, half and half, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture back into egg halves.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: tofu meatballs or patties
directions: Mash tofu; combine all ingredients and mix well.
Knead as dough 2 to 3 minutes.
Form into medium balls.
Bake in oiled dish at 425° for 30 minutes or until heated through and lightly browned.
Makes 18+ balls.
Place into spaghetti sauce.
Heat and serve over whole grain pasta.

title: sirloin tip roast
directions: Brown the roast in oil, searing the outside.
This will make a dark, rich gravy.
Add to this the other ingredients, especially the Kitchen Bouquet seasoning.
The Kitchen Bouquet gives the meat a wonderful flavor.
Cook in a pressure cooker for 30 minutes at 15 pounds pressure or cook in a Dutch oven for 2 hours on a medium heat.
Keep covered.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in slow oven at 350° until firm, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ant garden
directions: First take 1 piece of celery, then get smooth peanut butter and spread the peanut butter on the piece of celery.
Finally, put a few raisins on top of the peanut butter.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine as listed and bake at 350° for 1 hour in angel food pan.

title: pickled hot dogs
directions: Cut each hot dog into 3 pieces.
Heat Texas Pete, vinegar, water, sugar and salt in pan, mixing well.
Stir in hot dogs. Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often; do not boil.
Store in airtight container.
Drain before serving.

title: chicken pie with pour crust
directions: Boil and pick chicken.
Save broth and cook vegetables of choice in broth.
Mix chicken and vegetables together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: adam's applesauce
directions: Core apples; cut into quarters and peel.
Place apples in a large pan.
Cover with water.
Add cinnamon and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon. Remove from heat and mash until smooth.
Stir in sugar.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, add garlic and chili powder.
In oblong Pyrex
or
deep cookie sheet, line with tortillas then add
meat, tomatoes
and
soup.
Repeat layers, then top with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and some cherries on top.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix
first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in poppy seed. Bake in	a
loaf
pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until set in the center.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; chill until slightly set. Add remaining ingredients; fold in Cool Whip. Put into 2-quart dish and refrigerate until completely chilled. Adjust Jell-O flavors and fruit to suit your liking.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and orange juice alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a small greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stir-fried broccoli(ch'ao chieh lan)
directions: Separate broccoli florets with small stems from large florets and stalks.
Cut the large part into thin pieces about 1 1/2-inches long to make 6 cups in all.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Heat a wok until hot; add peanut oil and stir-fry the broccoli for about 2 minutes.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Add water and cover wok.
Cook over high heat for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Serve hot.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients and pat into quiche dish.
Bring milk and spices to preboil.
Add eggs and spinach.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn to 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn onto plate and slice into wedges.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thickened, then spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and chill for 2 to 3 hours. Be sure to keep covered.
Will keep refrigerated for several days.

title: potage chou-fleur
directions: Cook, drain and mash cauliflower.
Stir in soup and milk (in small amounts to prevent lumps).
Simmer 4 minutes.
Serve with sprinkled paprika on top.

title: gracies' biscuits
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening.
Add milk to mixture.
Roll out onto floured surface to about 1 1/2 inches thick and cut with floured cutter.
Dab tops with butter and bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes then reduce heat to 350 degrees for 5 more minutes.

title: best pickled beets
directions: Heat vinegar and water to boiling; add mustard, salt and sugar and blend; let boil.
Combine beets, onions, celery seed and spices.
Pour boiling vinegar over beets.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 15 minutes.

title: tex-mex chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 4 hours.
It's much better reheated the next day.

title: creamy cheese pie
directions: Beat the softened cream cheese. Gradually beat in the sugar. Add the sour cream and vanilla. Blend in the Cool Whip (about 1 3/4 cups).
Spoon into cooled, baked 9-inch graham cracker crust. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat together.
Place in a large kettle (about 4 quart size), than brown garlic, onions, and celery until tender and add to the meat, add tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Blend well, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Drain off fat when done.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle in layers: graham crackers, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts, then pour Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: billy goats cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop in small bits on lightly greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: coffee bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 15-inch pan.
Spread in mixture.
Top with chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry nut salad(low-fat)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; fold in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half the gelatin mixture into a loaf pan and refrigerate until firm, setting aside remaining gelatin at room temperature.
When set, spread yogurt over gelatin, then pour remaining gelatin over layer of yogurt. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Brush bottom of baking dish with stick of butter.
Layer with oysters, then whole saltine crackers.
Dot with butter.
Continue with another layer.
Scald milk.
Pour over all until covered. Bake in slow oven, 40 minutes or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add.
Mash bananas.
Add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan in oven at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 (1 pound) loaf.
Can make 2 smaller loaves.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and 1/2 stick margarine.
Melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of round cake pan. Arrange peaches over brown sugar in concentric circles.

title: zucchini torta
directions: Combine ingredients, adding onion and zucchini last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Saute garlic.
Cut up in olive oil.
Take out garlic.
Add all ingredients.
Fill empty paste can twice with water and add. Simmer about 35 minutes.
Add browned ground meat (drained of fat) before simmering.
Spread over cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda and spices.
Add eggs, pumpkin, water and oil; mix until well blended.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325° and bake 1 hour.
Excellent for freezing.

title: lemon pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and
lemon juice.
Then add cornstarch and egg yolks.
Bake in pie
shell.
Top with meringue with egg whites whipped.

title: never hard icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until it becomes very stiff.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth and creamy.

title: mary's baked beans
directions: Combine.
Put in oven about ten o'clock and will be done by four or five o'clock.

title: apple cupcakes
directions: Spray muffin pan with cooking spray.

title: short biscuits(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 300° to 350° (150° C).
Grease baking sheet. Sift flour, cornstarch and baking powder together.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add lightly beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, and mix well.
Take teaspoonful and roll into small balls.
Press down floured prongs of a fork.
Flour baking sheet to prevent spreading.
Bake approximately 15 minutes.
When cool, sandwich together with buttercream icing.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add water and dissolve.
Add raisins and cook.
When beginning to thicken, add vinegar and butter.
Pour in crust and top with another.

title: banana smoothy
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender; process until smooth.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, walnuts and butter.
Sprinkle mixture evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally to make crumbs.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; reserve remaining crumbs.
Beat egg whites until frothy; gradually add sugar and lemon juice, beating to stiff peaks.
Add Highland strawberries; continue beating until peaks reform.
Fold strawberry mixture into whipped cream.
Spoon over crumbs in prepared baking pan; top with reserved crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Cut in squares.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Great with sliced vegetables.

title: chicken confetti
directions: Season chicken with salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
In large skillet brown chicken in oil, then remove chicken.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in chicken and remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add water if necessary.
Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients.
Cook on low heat until it starts to bubble for 5 minutes.
Take off heat.

title: creole seasoning mix
directions: Mix in a small bowl.
Transfer mixture to small airtight jar. Makes 2/3 cup of seasoning.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add water and bouillon cubes or broth and heat to boiling.
Add noodles and cook 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic powder and cook 4 minutes.
Add milk and Velveeta cheese.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add extract and beat well.
Put fruit and nuts in large bowls.
Pour batter in and mix well.
Pour into 2 large greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until tested done.

title: hot cranberry drink
directions: Combine cranberry juice, water and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add spices; simmer 20 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in orange and lemon juice.
Yield: 2 quarts.

title: pork and noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cover noodles with ice water; let stand until thoroughly chilled.
Drain well.

title: chili-chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken and next 3 ingredients in hot oil in a Dutch oven until lightly browned. Add tomatoes and next 5 ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sour milk pancakes
directions: Beat together the sour milk, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Will keep for 1 to 2 weeks.
Makes 2 quarts.
Make pancakes and waffles.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Beat eggs. Blend in oil, vanilla and milk.
Add liquid to dry ingredients. Stir quickly just until moistened.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into well-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin tins or paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire rack.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: easy sausage strata
directions: Place sausage in a large, deep skillet; cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown. Drain and set aside.

title: jumbles(makes about 32 cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's mini baking bits, Hershey's mini chocolate chips, raisins and walnuts.

title: australian celery soup
directions: In a saucepan, mix the soup, water, milk and nutmeg.
Heat to boiling.
Serve hot, sprinkled with cheese.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and shortening in a 2-quart pan over low heat, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.

title: sugar-free ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients together.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Put potatoes in mixing bowl. Add sugar, syrup, cinnamon and salt. Beat with mixer. Add eggs and milk. Add melted butter and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes at high temperature. Then reduce to 350° and bake for 25 to 35 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: hunter's special
directions: Tear off a 14-inch length of aluminum foil.
Place tablespoon of butter in center of foil.
Slice onion, carrot and potato into one-quarter inch slices and arrange in center of foil.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Pat ground chuck into patty and place on top of vegetables.
Seal foil tightly and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven or on campfire on hot coals.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise, removing stem ends, seeds and membranes.
Immerse peppers into boiling water for 3 minutes. Sprinkle insides with salt.
Place on paper towel to drain well. In a skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, uncooked rice, Worcestershire sauce, basil, 1/2 cup water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup of cheese.
Fill peppers with meat mixture.
Place in baking dish and add any remaining meat mixture. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cool and serve.
Makes 4.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings in large bowl.
Add chicken breasts, cut in halves. Coat each piece well.
Let stand overnight.
Remove chicken from cream mixture, coat each piece in crumbs, place in baking pan and spoon half of melted butter over it.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Spoon rest of butter over chicken and bake 20 minutes or longer, until chicken is tender and brown.

title: marion's pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chops.
Dollop mushroom soup over chops.
Pour in beer.
Mix with mushroom soup to surround chops.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Serve with noodles, rice or mashed potatoes and green vegetable.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of the sugar and oleo. Press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with 2 tablespoons milk, remaining 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 of whip cream until smooth.
Fold into crust.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corns together; add eggs, sour cream and Jiffy mix.
Slice butter into pats and add to mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut "dream" cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9x13 pan. While cake is hot poke holes in top and pour eagle brand and cream of coconut over; let cool completely. Spread cool whip over top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: holiday cheese spread
directions: Blend ingredients together; form ball and refrigerate.
Serve with soda or snack crackers.
Keeps several weeks refrigerated.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat together egg and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into egg and milk mixture.
Stir in salad oil.
Stir all only until blended.
Batter should be lumpy!
Bake 'em and eat 'em.

title: george's fruit tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one gallon container; fill with water.
If you are freezing, leave 2 inches at the top to allow for expansion.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: grilled duck breasts
directions: Tenderize your duck breasts by applying meat tenderizer to both sides of duck breasts.
Marinate breasts in soy sauce for at least 1 hour.
Wrap breasts in bacon strips.
Grill over charcoal for 20 to 40 minutes.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: In a double boiler, combine candy bars and 1/2 cup of butter. Melt.
While candy melts, cream additional 1/2 cup of butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and soda mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan (this is too much batter for a 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.
Allow cake to cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown floured pork chops in skillet.
Peel and cut potatoes in slices.
Spread potatoes in a 9 x 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread celery or tomato soup over potatoes.
Pour milk over soup.
Place brown pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: campers' hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients and store.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook the Rice-A-Roni according to package instructions on box, except use 4 cups chicken broth instead of water. Mix all ingredients together and pour into a large casserole dish. Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash and onion.
Cook in a little water until just tender. Drain thoroughly.
Mash and add salt, pepper, sugar and eggs, most of the butter, saving a little to sprinkle on top.
Put into a buttered casserole, top with crumbs and melted butter over the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned (uncovered).
Even if you don't like squash, you'll probably like this!

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, flour and sugar.
Add flavoring and beat 10 minutes.
Cook in a 325° oven one hour or until done.
Leave in pan 30 minutes.

title: french chocolates
directions: In a double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, melt semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Stir in chopped walnuts, sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and dash of salt.
Cool mixture about 5 minutes.

title: ham loaf mix
directions: Thoroughly mix 1/3 cup of soup, meat, onions, bread cubes, eggs and mustard.
Shape into loaf.
Press pineapple deeply into the meat.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. In saucepan, blend remaining soup and sour cream.
Heat; stir now and then.
Serve over loaf.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage.
Melt cheese in crock-pot then add all ingredients and heat until melted.

title: monkey paws no. 2
directions: Melt oleo in 8-inch square pan.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn burner off.
Snip biscuits into fourths. Drop into syrup mixture and stir lightly to coat.
Pop into 350° oven and bake until top browns.
Turn out onto lightly buttered or Pam-sprayed platter.
Eat while warm, serves 2.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in jelly roll pan. Add single layer of potatoes, cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over the potatoes. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Add egg, mix well.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 8 x 10-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss all ingredients and serve with favorite dressing, salt and pepper.
Makes a pretty salad and is a great substitute for plain lettuce and tomato.

title: pineapple crush cake
directions: Make cake using directions on box.
Using 2 cake pans, split mix evenly.
Let cake cool and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: christy's shrimp newburg
directions: In large saucepan bring 1 quart of water and 3 tbsp. salt to boil. Add shrimp. Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer till shrimp turns pink, 1 to 3 minutes. Drain. Peel shrimp and remove black vein. Split peeled shrimp lengthwise.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt; stir to blend.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Add corn mixture and bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: grandma's emergency biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift.
Cut in shortening. Add milk gradually until a drop batter is formed.
Put in buttered tins and bake in 400° oven 10 or 15 minutes until brown.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Mix Tang, pudding mix and juice from pineapple.
Mixture will thicken as it stands.
Pour over pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, bananas and apples in a salad bowl.
Mix gently.
Store in refrigerator.
Bananas will not discolor.

title: texas chili
directions: In large skillet brown ground chuck, onions and green peppers. Drain.
Put rest of ingredients into a large pot.
Heat and add meat mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: cranberry pork roast for slow cooker
directions: Place pork roast in broiler pan and broil 15 to 20 minutes to remove excess fat.
Put browned pork roast in slow cooker.
In bowl, mix together cranberry sauce, sugar, cranberry juice, mustard and cloves.
Pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove roast and keep warm.
You should have about 2 cups of juices in slow cooker (add water if necessary).
Pour into saucepan and bring to boil.
Make a paste from the cornstarch and cold water and stir into juices.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Season with salt.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a quart jar and shake well.

title: black bean soup
directions: Rinse and drain the beans.
Put in a large pot with 1 1/2-quarts water and oil, bay leaf, clove, molasses, vingar and peppercorns.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.	Then crumble bacon.
Add onions to bacon
grease.
Add
beans; let fry a bit.	Mix ketchup and brown sugar together.
Add to skillet.
Stir, then remove from heat and pour
into	greased
pan.
Bake
in oven on 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Then serve!

title: fried bananas almondine
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Saute bananas and almonds in butter until golden brown.
Heat chocolate sauce and combine with orange liqueur.

title: dane's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cut into small pieces.
Melt oleo and mix with dressing mix.
Grease baking dish and layer 1/3 of dressing mix in dish.
Layer 1/2 of chicken on dressing.

title: over-the-rainbow macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine all shredded cheeses in a bowl and set aside.
Lightly butter a deep 2 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Boil enough water for 1 lb. macaroni.
Add oil and macaroni to boiling water.
Simmer 7 minutes and drain.
Put macaroni back in pot.
Melt one stick butter in sauce pan and stir into macaroni.
Add half and half, 1 1/2 c. shredded cheeses, Velveeta and eggs.
Season with pepper and seasoned salt.
Transfer to casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheeses and butter.
Bake until bubbles at edges, about 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: smoked pork shoulder and spiced fruit sauce *
directions: Select the smoked pork shoulder.
Roll and cover the meat with water.
Slice onion and add the onion, whole cloves and stick cinnamon to the meat.
Cover the meat tightly and simmer it 2 hours.
Remove the meat from the cooking liquid.
Slice meat and serve hot with Spiced Fruit Sauce in orange cups.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: In large saucepan, stir together frozen vegetables, chicken broth, onion, mustard and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 7 to 10 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown ribs; pour off fat.
In a bowl, mix rest of ingredients. Pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water, shaking off excess.
Shake a few potatoes at a time in bag, coating well.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in 2 cups boiling water.
Add to jello: drained pineapple (save juice), bananas, marshmallows and nuts. Put in refrigerator and congeal.
Cook pineapple juice and water (enough to make 1 cup), 1/2 cup sugar, 1 egg and 2 tablespoons flour.
Cool mixture.
May set overnight and fold into Cool Whip next morning.
Spread on top of jello.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour. Serve as dessert or as a salad.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add the soda, eggs, vanilla and milk;
mix well.
Pour into a large 18 x 12 x 1-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Boil exactly 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Chop celery, pepper, onion and pimento.
Drain vegetables; mix salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar, water and oil.
Bring to boil until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool; pour over vegetables and mix.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: aunt sara's easter cake
directions: Melt oleo, sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Mix it together.
Now put flour in bowl.
Add the mixture from saucepan.
Now add baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Knead this dough well.
If dough is too soft, add more flour.
If dough is too stiff, add more milk.
Roll dough into a rope form and shape it into any shape desired.
You can make it like a basket and put a raw egg in center.
Beat 1 egg. This is to be brushed onto dough before baking.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Basket is made by putting one rope on top of the other, make it so some dough is under the egg.
You can make braids and then make a cross with egg.

title: texas dills
directions: Mix water, vinegar and salt well.
Put in quart jars the dill, allspice, mustard and red pepper.
Pack pickles loose in jars. Pour cold brine over pickles.
Put on lids and put into boiling water for 3 minutes.
Take out and tighten lids down.

title: cream cheese blueberry dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Soften cream cheese and beat until smooth. Add well beaten eggs and remaining sugar and vanilla. Cream well. Pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Chill. Spread blueberry filling on top.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on full power for 3 minutes, stopping twice to stir. Serve with sourdough pretzels. Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, Crisco, egg. Mix in flour, cover with tight lid and put in refrigerator at least 2 hours or overnight.
Dough will rise often, so check and mash down.
Repeat as long as in refrigerator.
Keeps 3 days in refrigerator.
Take out of refrigerator.
Make into rolls
and let rise 1 1/2 hours before baking at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Measure first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan and bring it to a boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper until set. Makes about 3 dozen.
Please remember to have adult supervision when using a stove.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine and mix all the ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch tin.
Bake in oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Make sure that you use Knorr vegetable soup.
It makes a difference in the flavor.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Pull chicken from bone.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Layer pieces of chicken on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour the soup and sour cream mixture over the chicken.
Pour the crushed Ritz crackers over the soup mixture.
Melt butter or margarine and drizzle it on top of the Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl. Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and eggs.
Beat real good.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake for 1 hour or until center is firm.
Cool to room temperature.
Spread with strawberry glaze (optional).
Chill for 3 hours.
Loosen edge of cheesecake with knife before removing from pan.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot and cook until tender.
When done, add jar of Cheez Whiz.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients, except milk. Add milk last; pour into pastry shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve chilled.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: In a sturdy plastic bag, place 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs or crushed cornflakes, 1 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon each of poultry seasoning, garlic powder and pepper and 1 teaspoon made up of one or a combination of the following:
thyme, basil and oregano.
Add salt to taste.
Blend ingredients well by shaking and pour off about a quarter of the contents into another plastic bag.
Shake two or three pieces of chicken at a time in the second bag until well coated, and you'll be all set to bake.

title: microwave cashew brittle
directions: Mix cashews, sugar and Karo. Microwave until it is tan in color. (Takes about 10 minutes.) Then add butter and vanilla. Stir well and microwave another 2 to 3 minutes until it is CARAMEL colored. Then add baking soda, mix well, and spread thinly in a buttered cookie sheet. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Melt oleo or butter in the 9 x 13-inch pan in which you plan to bake this.
Pan should also be sprayed with Pam.
Boil the water, berries, sugar and cornstarch together until thick and clear.
Pour this over crust which has been baked and cooled.
Pour over at least 3 more cups of sliced berries.
The crust of oleo or butter, flour and sugar is mixed and patted thinly over bottom of pan. Bake at 300° until golden.

title: jaunita's mandarin cake
directions: Pour cake mix in large bowl.
Add juice from both cans of oranges, 4 eggs and oil.
Gently fold in Mandarin oranges.
Spray cake pan with Pam and bake cake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake should be completely cool before icing.

title: veal scallopini with marsala
directions: Pound veal scallops lightly with a mallet if they are too thick.
Dredge each in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Over medium heat melt butter and oil together.
Add veal and turn up heat slightly.
Saute, turning frequently until veal is browned on all sides; remove veal to separate plate.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the pan drippings.
Add the finely minced green onions and saute until translucent.
Add the sliced mushrooms and scrape bottom of pan to bring up any juices.
Put in veal scallops, wine and beef bouillon.
Bring mixture to a boil, then turn heat down to very low; cover and let simmer for approximately 12 minutes until sauce is thickened.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in a pot; cover with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and let simmer until tender.
Drain and place in a mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper. Beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in 2 cups cheese, bacon and onions.
Put potatoes in a greased baking dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and potatoes are heated through.

title: new old-fashioned cherry cheesecake*
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Add dry milk, sugar substitute and vanilla.
Blend in 1/2 cup reduced-cal topping.
Spread evenly over bottom of pie crust; chill.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all together except 1/2 cup cheese.
Put cheese on top and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: ham or turkey casserole
directions: Combine turkey or ham, soup and milk.
Heat to boiling. Grease two-quart casserole and spread 1 1/2 cups potato chips on the bottom.
Pour in the turkey mixture.
Cover with remaining potato chips.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika over top.
Bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: pillsbury's cranberry free freeze(recipe may be halved)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Spoon into 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Freeze.
Let soften slightly before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add carrots, liquid and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Let cool on cooling rack.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix
lemonade mix, cream of coconut, coconut flavoring, sugar and
pineapple
juice in a gallon container.
A milk jug or carton is good to use.
Finish filling container with water and freeze. Take out 5 hours ahead of time to thaw.

title: hawaiian style shoyu chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Brown chicken, drain fat. Add ingredients from bowl to pot.
Let it simmer for 1 hour until chicken is tender.
Place chicken on platter, garnish with scallions.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: After mixing the meats thoroughly, add egg, milk and bread crumbs and mix with meat.
Place in greased pan and bake for 1 hour in a medium oven of 350°.

title: cold carrot salad
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Bring to a boil, vinegar, sugar and can tomato soup (undiluted).
Pour over drained carrots.
Add minced celery, onion and bell pepper.
Stir well.
Marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs; blend with other ingredients.
Stir in broccoli. Pour into baking dish.
Top with 1 stick margarine mixed with 1 stack Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Spread over mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut-almond cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. In large bowl, cream the butter and shortening with the sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

Add flour and remaining liquid ingredients. In blender or food processor, chop coconut to a firm texture.	Fold into cake batter. Pour in cake pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until tester comes out clean. Serves 16.

title: salsa delite
directions: Put seasoning mix in pan with 1/2 to 3/4 c. water.
Bring to boil.
Add rest of ingredients; stir and serve in bowl to dip taco chips or potato chips.

title: frozen berry jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook on High for 5 minutes; stir.
Reduce power setting to Medium and cook 8 minutes.
Stir well.
Let cool.
Freeze the berries you pick, but add another cup
of sugar.
You can double the recipe.
Two cups fresh berries equals about 10 ounce frozen package.
If doubling recipe, use 3-quart casserole.

title: pepper relish
directions: Halve, seed and chop peppers with coarse knife in food chopper. Add salt and let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain well.
Add other vegetables in large enamel or stainless kettle.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices in a cloth bag.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Place in sterile jars.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water.
Seal.

title: sonny's pie crust
directions: Carrots, walnuts and raisins provide color, texture and interesting flavors in these muffins.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Fold into pumpkin mixture. Spread on greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool, then unroll.
Spread filling over cake; cool again and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: holiday coffee cake
directions: Drain cherries:
discard juice or save for another use. Reserve 10 cherries for garnish.
Chop remaining cherries. Combine cherries, cream cheese, almonds, sugar and almond extract.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; saute the onions over low heat until brown. Blend in flour; add broth, wine, salt and pepper, mixing steadily to the boiling point. Cover loosely. Decrease heat. Cook for 25 minutes. Serve with Swiss cheese and French bread or croutons.

title: agee's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add 1 egg at a time until you use 4.
Gradually add flour, beating well.
Add 2 remaining eggs.
Beat thoroughly, adding vanilla and almond flavoring.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Blend with mixer.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans, if you like.

title: plantation pie(cake dessert)
directions: Beat well egg, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla, milk and butter; beat in flour, baking powder and salt.
Place fruit in 6-cup baking dish or cake pan.
Pour cake mixture over fruit and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup sugar on top of cake batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
