title: ground beef or pork appetizers
directions: Cook meat in frypan until it loses pink color.
Remove excess fat. Add lime or lemon juice, fish sauce, ground hot chili, sugar and ginger.
Stir in and cook for a couple of minutes.
Add onion last and cook just until wilted.
Garnish pork with roasted peanuts. Serve with loose-leaf lettuce as described in Thai Beef Appetizer recipe.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Add beaten egg yolks, sugar, salt and spices to pumpkin. Gradually add scalded milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: layered salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce.
Tear into bite size pieces and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice celery and sprinkle over lettuce.
Next, put a layer of 1 cup of the cheese.
Place sliced onion on next. In small bowl, mix the sour cream and sugar together and spread over salad.
Then, mix the mayonnaise and vinegar and drizzle over that.
Crumble the bacon over it next. Top with remaining cup of cheese.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: toasty onion spread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread mixture on Triscuits and place under the broiler until brown and bubbly.

title: french onion soup
directions: You may use any cheese of your taste.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: In large kettle cover beef with water and add chopped onion, salt and thyme.
Bring to boil.
Skim fat from surface.
Add split peas, cover and simmer over low heat, 3 to 4 hours.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Adjust seasoning.
Serves 8.

title: cherry-pineapple ice cream
directions: Cut cherries in half.
Mix cherries and pineapple together. Add condensed milk, 1 cup regular milk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Using electric mixer or blender, mix well.
Add sugar and milk until mixture is as sweet as you like.
Freeze, using ice cream freezer.

title: double chip bars
directions: Place butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; place in a heated 350° oven until melted.
Remove from the oven.
Sprinkle the cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Sprinkle with chips; press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack before cutting.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Measure croutettes; crush slightly and toss in melted oleo. Set aside.
Place broccoli, water and salt in saucepan and bring to boil; separate pieces.
Remove from heat and drain; set aside. Place cheese and soup in saucepan (or microwave).
Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into ungreased casserole (1 1/2-quart); sprinkle croutons over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat, celery, onion and salt.
In a separate pot, cook cabbage for 5 minutes.
After it starts boiling, drain and add to meat mixture.
Add rice and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread-and-butter zucchini or cucumber pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart glass bowl and microwave 7 to 9 minutes on High, stirring twice, until vegetables are crisp-tender and onion is translucent.
Ladle into a hot, clean jar and cover.
Cool slightly and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine bean sprouts, spinach, water chestnuts, onion and eggs in bowl.
Add bacon.
Shake together sugar, salad oil, worcestershire sauce, catsup and vinegar.
Pour over spinach mixture.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn; cool and cut from cob.
Add chopped cabbage, onions and peppers.
Mix dry ingredients; add vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and simmer for 40 minutes.
Put in hot jar; seal.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In a bowl, beat cream cheese smooth with fork. Stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper and salt.
Chill. Shape into a ball and roll in remaining 1 cup pecans.
Chill again.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze according to freezer manufacturer's directions.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Ready to serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings. Dip chicken in combined egg and milk, then coat with cheese mixture. Place in baking dish. Pour margarine over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brenda's hawaiian chicken with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, mix pineapple, cherries, juices and walnuts.
Heat on low until fruits and nuts soften slightly, also allowing flavors to mingle.
Meanwhile, rinse chicken thighs and pat dry.
Lightly brush honey onto thighs, arranging in shallow baking dish.
Pour 3/4 of contents of saucepan over chicken, spreading fruits and nuts evenly.
Reserve 1/4.
Bake chicken at 400° for approximately 1 hour (until fully cooked and juices are evaporated).
Turn chicken occasionally.
Stir fruits and nuts.
Cook rice.
Serve with chicken as side dish.
Use 1/4 reserved juices, etc. to serve warm over rice.
Good with frozen peas.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot slaw
directions: Cook cabbage, then add vinegar and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Let simmer awhile.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter over medium heat.
Blend together flour and milk.
Gradually stir into onion and cook 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and half and half.
Heat to boiling.
Gradually add cheese, stirring constantly until melted.
Stir in pepper.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch glass pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.
When done, remove from oven and top with 1 can of cherries or whatever fruit you like.

title: collaci(serves 8)
directions: In
a
large
skillet,	fry
bacon
until just browned; remove with a slotted spoon and drain on a paper towel.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: In skillet, brown sausage; drain off grease and break up in large pieces.
In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Tear bread into small pieces and add to egg mixture. Add cheese and sausage.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake casserole at 350° until puffy and golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 4 layered delight
directions: *Two small boxes or for more pudding, 1 large and 1 small box. You can also substitute butterscotch pudding for chocolate.

title: heard it through the grapevine (salad)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together in a large bowl. Wash broccoli, cut off tops and put them in bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Add bacon.
Chop onion finely.
Add onion.
Add raisins.
Mix all ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: waffles
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder, dash of salt and dash of nutmeg. Add the eggs, milk and oil. Cook on hot griddle.

title: baskin robbins pie
directions: Mix in mixer.
Pat in glass 10 x 6-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375° until light brown.
Cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz and mayonnaise.
Drain vegetables and mix with Cheez Whiz and mayonnaise.
Put in large dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Put on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Trim and cook asparagus and broccoli and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Slice and saute mushrooms in large buttered baking dish. Pour melted butter over vegetables.
Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Gruyere cheese and ham.
Cover with beaten eggs.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until eggs are set and top is golden brown.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Combine gelatin and hot water.
Cut mandarin oranges into pieces.
Stir oranges and pineapple into gelatin.
Fold in sour cream.
Put into mold; chill until firm.

title: peanut butter ball
directions: Melt wax and bits (chocolate) into double boiler. Mix the rest together and make small ball. Keep wax and bits (chocolate) over low heat. Dip ball into mix, using 2 forks to remove. Let drip and dry on wax paper. Makes 50 balls.

title: mother's not-so-hot chili
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic.
Add paprika, oregano, salt, red and black pepper and chili powder.
Mix well.
Add beef broth and tomatoes.
Cook 1 hour.
Drain beans.
Add and cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: happy day cake
directions: Place sifted flour in sifter.
Add sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir shortening in bowl to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add 3/4 cup milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs, vanilla and rest of milk.
Beat 1 minute more.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Mix the mustard and currant jelly and place in the top of a double boiler.
Diagonally slice in 1/2-inch thickness the frankfurters; add them to the sauce and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot on cocktail picks.
May be frozen.

title: toffee bar cake
directions: Sift flour, wheat germ, baking powder and salt. Set aside. Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg substitute. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add mashed bananas.
Mix all ingredients, alternating dry and moist, adding nuts and vanilla last.
Bake at 325° for approximately 35 minutes.
Length of time to prepare:
1 hour.
Number of servings: 16 to 18.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: Place watermelon cubes in blender or food processor and blend until smooth (approximately 3 cups of mixture).
Stir in sugar. In a saucepan, combine gelatin and juice cocktail.
Add to melon mixture.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover and freeze for 2 hours or until firm.
Break up frozen mixture and place in a bowl.
Beat with mixer on medium/high speed or until mixture is fluffy.
Return to pan.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours or until firm.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown meats.
Add onions and cook slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add bean sprouts and cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat and let cool (30 minutes).

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press down slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Stir ingredients together and fry in patties.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 2 small pies or one deep-dish pie. Bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken bombay
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and put into 2 large skillets with 2 tablespoons butter in each. Saute until light gold.
Remove chicken; add onion to fat in one pan.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, mashing tomatoes with spoon.
Add all chicken.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken is tender.
If you are preparing in advance, simmer only 5 minutes, then cool and refrigerate (may be frozen).
Simmer 15 minutes or so.
Serve hot over rice.

title: yam bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil yams until tender, then drain and mash well.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and salt.
Set aside.
Next, cream butter and brown sugar in a large bowl until light.
Add eggs one at a time to mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add half of dry ingredients and stir well, then add half of the half and half and stir well.
Repeat the same steps with the rest of the dry ingredients and half and half.
Add mashed yams and vanilla and beat well.
Pour into buttered 8 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish and bake in middle shelf of oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Add sugar, flour and cocoa; stir.
Then add milk, butter and vanilla.
Wait until it thickens, then it is done.
(Medium to low.)

title: moo shu pork
directions: Marinate pork with soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger root.
Set aside. In preheated skillet, put 2 tablespoons oil.
Scramble eggs to make thin omelet.

Cool and cut into thin strips. Set aside. Add additional 2 tablespoons oil to skillet and brown pork. Stir-fry for 1 minute. Add sliced mushrooms and cook 2 minutes. Add chicken broth and seasonings. Thicken slightly with cornstarch. Transfer to platter.
Add egg strips and shredded green onions.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix powdered sugar, oleo and peanut butter together.
Form into 1-inch balls and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, sugar and nuts.
Pour melted butter over all and mix until you can pat it out in a pizza pan. Bake at 370° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
Cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to the directions on box.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Place the dough balls in ungreased Bundt pan or tube pan. Sprinkle the dry pudding over rolls.
Melt together the sugar and butter; pour over pudding.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts. Cover with towel; let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until done.
Remove from oven; let set about 5 minutes, then flip onto plate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and pinch together. Bake until light brown.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine berries and pie filling; pour into cooked, cooled, deep dish pie shell.
Chill before serving.
Top with Cool Whip. Makes 2 pies.

title: cajun chicken jambalaya
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Sprinkle with salt.
In a large non-stick skillet, heat oil to medium high.
Cook chicken 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove chicken
from skillet.
In same skillet, cook green peppers, 3/4 of scallions and celery for 5 minutes or until pepper is crisp-tender.
Add rice to skillet and cook stirring, 1 minute.
Return chicken to skillet.
Stir in bacon, salsa and broth.

Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice has absorbed liquid and internal juices of chicken runs clear. (Meat thermometer should read 180 degrees in thickest part of chicken.)

title: smoked sausage soup
directions: Cook onion and celery in a little oil until tender.
Add to tomatoes, beans, chicken broth, thyme and basil.
Cook about 2 hours.
Add smoked sausage and cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, spices and cocoa. Cream well. Add eggs, beating well after each addition. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour over fruit. Add flour with soda alternately with applesauce, beating until smooth.
Last add the nuts and raisins to batter. Bake in angel food pan or 10 x 10-inch loaf pan for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Very moist and does not need icing.

title: deviled steak
directions: Flour, salt, pepper and Accent steak pieces; fry in hot oil until brown, but not done.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute.
Mix remaining ingredients and return steak to skillet.
Pour mixture over steak and stir.
Cover tightly and simmer approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add a little water if needed during cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil, then add egg and pumpkin. Mix well. Then add dry ingredients. Add orange juice and nuts. Bake at 350 degrees. Will make two 9 x 13 cakes or a pound cake.

title: supreme chicken saute l'orange
directions: *Cream may be brought to boil (scald) and allowed to simmer for 30 minutes prior to dish preparation.

title: herbed spaghetti squash
directions: Wash squash; cut in half lengthwise.
Remove and discard seeds. Place squash, cut sides down, in a Dutch oven.
Add water to pan to a depth of 2 inches.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until squash is tender.
Drain squash; let cool.
Using a fork, remove spaghetti-like strands from squash; discard shells.
Place strands in a serving bowl; add parsley and next 5 ingredients and toss gently.
Garnish with a fresh basil sprig, if desired.
Yields 8 servings (29 calories and 25% fat per 1/2 cup serving).

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy. Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly, but well. Mix remaining ingredients, except nuts, in a separate bowl. Add flour mixture to the first mixture and blend. Fold in nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: chili cheese bars
directions: Grate and mix cheeses together.
Line bottom of a 9-inch square ovenproof dish with half of the cheese mixture.
Spread green chilies and juice over cheese mixture.
Layer remaining cheese. Pour eggs over cheeses and chili mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars or squares.
For a spicier appetizer, add cayenne pepper.

title: best-ever meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, except bacon slices.
When well blended, turn into a greased, shallow baking pan.
With your hands wet, shape mixture into a rounded loaf.
Arrange 4 pieces of bacon on top of loaf.
Bake on the center rack of the oven at 350° for about 1 hour, or until brown.
We like to coat the top of the loaf with catsup 15 minutes before cooking is done.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, raisins and nuts (after the broccoli has been peeled).

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Combine oleo, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix real good.
Add buttermilk, cinnamon, vanilla, eggs and soda; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured shallow 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend milk, pudding mix and sweetened condensed milk.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas, then put on prepared pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain
beans.
Combine
green
peppers, onion rings and pimento.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill overnight.

title: praline coffee
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven, combine coffee, milk and sugar. Stirring occasionally, cook over medium-high heat until mixture just begins to boil; remove from heat and add ice cream, vanilla and maple flavoring.
Serve hot.
Yields twenty 6-ounce servings.

title: glazed carrots with onion and bacon
directions: Boil carrots, covered, in a small amount of water until crisp-tender and drain.
Cook bacon in a skillet until crisp, drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in reserved drippings, until tender. Add pepper, brown sugar and carrots.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange and apricot salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapple and juice with strained apricots and sugar.
Heat until hot, but not boiling; stir constantly.
Add gelatin to hot mixture; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool to thicken.

title: next best thing to robert redford pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine together and press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place breasts, tomatoes and mushrooms in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt together.
Set aside. Beat eggs, sugar, oil together.
Add vanilla and mix in flour mixture.
Add bananas, vanilla and nuts; pour into a greased and flour loaf pan.

title: shrimp and garlic pasta
directions: Cook the Pasta Accents according to the package directions, omitting the water and putting the butter on top of pasta before cooking.
Saute shrimp in butter.
Mix together for a fast and easy main dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Divide into 2 balls.
Chill 30 minutes for easy handling.
Roll each ball in chopped nuts. Serve one, freeze the other for a special time.
Each ball serves 8.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: breakfast brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and crumble; drain well.
Beat eggs, salt, mustard and milk.
In a large Pyrex dish, layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be made ahead; freezes well.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Layer rest of ingredients in order.
(Mix taco seasoning into sour cream.) Serve with Frito dip chips or tortilla chips.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown onions and beef.
Add all other ingredients except noodles and stir gently until well mixed.
Turn into 3-quart casserole and top with noodles.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: aunt june's pound cake
directions: Let cream cheese, Parkay and eggs get to room temperature. Cream together cream cheese and Parkay. Add 1 cup flour, 2 eggs and 1 cup sugar and mix well. Repeat this two more times. Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: straw cookies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll out, cut out and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread dip on sliced ham.
Roll up longways and slice.
Put a toothpick through each one.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: frog legs
directions: first I would need to get my pot of water.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: pig's feet soup
directions: Add pig's feet, salt, ginger, and pepper to boiling water. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
In another pot boil squash until tender.
Remove, drain and mash squash.
Add squash, tomatoes, and lima beans to soup mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for approximately 15 minutes.
Serves 3 to 5. Big Mama's best and healthy soup.

title: the darby's special oven fried chicken with rice
directions: Cut up fryer.
Salt, pepper and flour.
Place in a casserole with oleo.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken over and cook another 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: christmas chow
directions: You will need 1 brown grocery sack (big).

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour into raisin mixture and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake.

title: cheesy-creamy stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake the potatoes until soft. Cut in half lengthwise. Scoop out the potatoes in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixed.
Re-fill potato skins or foil potato holders.
Reheat under broiler.
Serves 6 or 12.

title: jamaican pork tenderloin
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Combine lime juice and next 5 ingredients in a large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Add pork; seal bag and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Remove pork from bag reserving marinade.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place over medium coals.
Place pork on rack; cover and cook 27 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 160°, turning and basting pork occasionally.
Cut into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Serve with chutney.

title: supper-in-a-hurry
directions: This is a good way to use leftovers!

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel avocado and remove pit.
Place avocado meat in bowl, mash with fork.
Peel and dice tomato.
Add tomato, onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic; mixing well.
Blend in sour cream.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Use toothpick for doneness.
When cool, serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: tex-mex corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 8-inch skillet and place in oven to heat.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, beating well.
Pour batter into prepared skillet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
This corn bread is very moist. Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: choked off biscuits
directions: Sift flour into large plastic or wooden bowl.
Make a nest in the middle and put Crisco in the nest.
(Cooking oil may be used.) Pour buttermilk over Crisco and squeeze flour and Crisco to mix with buttermilk.
When batter is ready to knead, flip in more flour by working around the edge, until dough is of the consistency to pinch off biscuit-size chunks.
Roll biscuits in palm of hands to smooth.
Spray a baking pan large enough for 12-15 biscuits with Pam and very gently arrange in pan.
Press down to smooth.
Bake at 425-450 degrees for 15-20 minutes until top starts to brown.
Turn oven off and leave in oven for another 5-10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown venison cubes in hot bacon drippings in heavy Dutch oven.
Add water to cover, seasonings and onion.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours.

title: peach ribbon pie
directions: Peach layers:
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water. Chill until partially set.
Sprinkle lemon juice over sliced peaches.

title: dill dip(good with raw vegetables)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water as directed on package.
Add other ingredients.
Add mayonnaise last.
Mold in an 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: pigs in the blanket
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll up in blanched cabbage.

title: strawberry-rhubarb jell-o salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries, undrained rhubarb and pineapple.
Set in refrigerator till thickened.
Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Blend in softened cream cheese to topping.
Pour onto top of Jell-O mixture and sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.	Let set for 3 hours.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge orange cappuccino
directions: In a 4-quart heavy saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, bring the sugar, salt, butter and milk to a full boil. Boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Off heat, add the chocolate and marshmallow cream.
Stir vigorously and speedily until chocolate is melted and mixture is a uniform color.
At once, stir in the nuts and pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm enough to cut into large squares or bars; wrap each individually.
Keep stored in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: pork chops jardiniere
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in hot oil in a large skillet; drain pan drippings.
Put bouillon cubes in boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour over pork chops in skillet.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over mashed potatoes if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: episcopal punch
directions: Boil sugar and water
16 minutes or until mixture spins thread.
Add pineapple juice,
orange and lemon juice to sugar syrup.
Add enough water
to
make	4
quarts
of liquid.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over ice.

title: potato delicious
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes just enough to separate; melt oleo and saute onion.
Add milk, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper and about 1/2 of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 325°. Uncover and sprinkle rest of cheese on top; bake 15 minutes more.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Mix water and gelatin. Let sit about 1 minute. Heat over low heat until gelatin is dissolved. Add cream cheese, soup and Worcestershire sauce. Heat over low heat until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased mold and chill. Remove from mold and serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, combine peanut butter, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Add corn flakes and Rice Krispies; mix.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or jelly roll pan.
Do not grease pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and spread while warm. May need to put into oven for a few minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: no peek skillet chicken
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil and brown chicken; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms and garlic.
Combine with soup mix. Simmer, covered, 45 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Makes six servings.
Serve with hot noodles, hot bread and salad.

title: yogurt cream pie
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Stir well until completely dissolved.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add yogurt and stir until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and stir until well blended. Pour into the graham cracker crust and chill in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours before serving.
All ingredients can be low-fat or fat-free and it is just as good!

title: peach cobbler
directions: To well beaten egg, add sugar and peaches.
Spread on butter baking dish.
Dot over with butter.
Cover with biscuit dough. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "poppy seed" loaf
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix together and bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate on High 1 minute.
Stir and microwave 30 seconds more.
Add cocoa and stir until all chocolate is melted. In food processor, chop prunes and water until prunes puree to thick paste.
Add egg whites, sugar and chocolate.
Process until smooth.
In small bowl, mix flour, salt and soda.
Add to chocolate mixture and process with quick pulses, just until blended.
Spray an 8-inch square pan with Pam.
Spread mixture evenly into pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: open-faced raisin pie
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add vanilla and flour. Add raisins and about 1/2 cup water they were cooked in.
Add the nuts.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Mix sugar, egg, vanilla, and flour.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: orange salad surprise
directions: Mix in order given.
Set in refrigerator for about 3 hours.

title: diane's apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake until topping is golden brown.
Apples will be tender.
Approximate baking time is 30 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or your favorite ice cream.
Makes 6 servings, 295 calories per serving.

title: meridian cooler
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a large punch bowl.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: lemon snow bars
directions: Stir together 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar; cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Pat into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; beat well.

title: orange ice cream soda
directions: In a pitcher, combine punch and soda.
Pour into tall glasses; top each with a scoop of ice cream.

title: hiking bread
directions: To Make Bread:
Whisk flours with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat yogurt, brown sugar and molasses with electric mixer until smooth.
Add oats.
Beat on medium speed again.
Stir in flour and raisins by hand until combined.

title: no bake cake
directions: Break cakes into pieces.
Place cake into bottom of pan.
Mix pudding and pour over cake pieces.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding and cake.
Spread cherry pie filling on top of this.
Let set in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: whacky cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Put in vinegar, vanilla and water and mix well.
Pour in greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 33 minutes.
Use any kind of white icing.

title: graham cracker snack
directions: Mix together and serve on graham crackers.

title: gracie burgess' pound cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, about 1/2 at a time, beating constantly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chess pie
directions: Optional:
May use 1/2 cup of brown sugar if preferred.
But if using brown sugar, use 3/4 cup white sugar instead of 1 cup along with the brown sugar.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine all ingredients except Seven-Up.
Freeze 5 or 6 hours in a large bowl. Serve mushy in Seven-Up.
Makes 20 servings.

title: zesty hot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter. Add vinegar and hot pepper sauce. Place chicken in baking dish. Pour mixture over chicken. Sprinkle Hidden Valley Ranch mix over chicken. Bake 35-40 minutes, until tender.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: In a large stainless steel saucepan, warm milk (rinsing with cold water before adding milk prevents milk burn) at medium heat to scalding (just short of boiling).
Remove and cool at least 1 hour to barely lukewarm.
In each of two clean quart jars, place 2 tablespoons of commercial yogurt (Dannon) for starter.
Divide milk between jars and stir gently.
Place the jars in a warm place (80° to 110°).
Should incubate from 8 to 16 hours.
Test yogurt by tipping the jar slightly.
If it leaves the side of the jar and is thick, it is ready to be covered and refrigerated.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's. Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2 inch pieces.
Stir 1 cup sugar and 2 Tbsp. flour together and mix with rhubarb.
Put in pan and dot with butter.
Mix remaining sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Stir in beaten egg.
Put on top of rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ginger spice cutout cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar and add molasses; beat in egg and add vinegar.
Mix well.
Add flour and all spices; blend thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out cookies. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes; do not overbake.

title: texas delite
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, nuts and oleo.
Spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: curried spinach soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potato and green onion in 2 tablespoons of the butter over medium heat, about 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Slowly add spinach, one-fifth at a time, stirring just until spinach is limp and dark green after each addition.
In a food processor or blender, process or blend spinach mixture, half at a time, until smooth.
In the same saucepan, melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter over medium heat. Stir in flour and curry powder; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Slowly add broth, whisking until combined.
Stir in spinach mixture and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is slightly thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 1 minute more.
In a medium bowl, stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into sour cream.
Return mixture to saucepan.
Heat through but do not boil.
Top with croutons, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease or spray 1 (8-inch) square cake pan.
Pour filling on bottom and sprinkle cake mix over.
Then drizzle oleo on top.
Can add nuts to top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Stir in sugar, egg yolks and lemon juice and rind.
Add flour, butter, milk, egg whites and fold in gently.
Bake in deep dish crust for 375 for 30-40 minutes or until top is brown.

title: acini di pepe
directions: Drain the pineapple and the oranges and save the juices.
Cook the di pepe as directed on the box.
Drain
and mix it with the pudding.
Cool.
Add the fruit, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix well and serve with tray of vegetables.

title: navy bean soup as you like it(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Put olive oil in soup pot and simmer sausage for 30 minutes. Drain soaking water from beans and add beans to sausage along with 3 quarts of water.
Add other ingredients, except seasoning. Simmer, simmer, simmer; stir occasionally.
Add water, if necessary.
Add spices 30 minutes before serving.

title: pancakes
directions: Put flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl. Combine eggs, milk and oil or butter; add to dry ingredients.
Beat quickly only until large lumps disappear.
If batter thickens upon standing, thin with 1/4 to 1/2 cup milk.
Bake on 375° griddle until bubbles break and edges are cooked.
Turn and bake other side.
Serve immediately.
Yields 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, 2 1/2 cups of milk and dry mustard.
In a separate bowl combine soup, remaining milk and salt.
In a large cake pan (12 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch) layer cubed bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour eggs, milk and mustard over all.
Top with soup mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce congealed salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add Jell-O; stir until well mixed.
Add pineapple and nuts and pour into mold.

title: apple crisp
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Place apples in an 8-inch pan.
Mix rest of the ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle on top of the apples. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: coleslaw
directions: Stir vinegar into mayonnaise.
Add salt and sugar.
Add to grated cabbage.
May add grated carrot for color.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Place meat balls in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat balls. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix together and put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add butter and stir well.
Mix together flour, oatmeal and baking soda.
Mix all together and divide in 2 (9-inch) cake tins.
Bake in a preheated 250° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Put together with strawberry preserves and let stand for a day or two.
Melt chocolate and spread on top.

title: yogurt sip
directions: Let peaches stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
In a blender container, combine yogurt, brandy, rum and honey.
Add undrained peaches. Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses. Top with nutmeg.

title: blue cheese sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in dish.
Top with chips or corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon and onion over bottom of pie crust.
Add half the ham, then half the cheese.
Then rest of ham and rest of cheese
on top of that.
Beat eggs and mustard, slowly add the hot cream, stirring constantly.
Pour this over the top of cheese. Let
stand	10 minutes.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and bake	at 350°.
Test
after 25 minutes with toothpick.
Total time to bake, 45 minutes.
Cool slightly, cut into slices.

title: blankenheim restaurant swiss steaks
directions: Mix flour and seasoned salt in dish.
Pound meat with tenderizer hammer on both sides, then cut into 6 to 8 pieces.
Dip into seasoned flour mixture.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with a nonfat cooking spray.
Beat evaporated skim milk, Egg Beaters and flour together until smooth.
Split open chiles and rinse to remove seed.
Drain chiles on paper towel.
Mix cheeses together and reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Alternate layers of chiles, cheese and Egg Beaters mixture in casserole dish.
Pour chunky tomatoes over top layer and sprinkle reserved cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour or until done in the center.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: *Just add enough of these ingredients for flavor.

title: "dump" cake
directions: "Dump" cake mix into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread evenly.
Spread pie filling on top.
Pour melted butter over fruit. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Do not mix!
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins(low-fat)
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in cereal.
Add buttermilk, oil, applesauce and egg whites.
Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not stir batter again.
Store overnight before baking.
Mixture may be stored in refrigerator in a non-metal container for up to 6 weeks.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Flake shrimp with fork and mix with other ingredients.
Let set for at least 1/2 hour.
Add mayonnaise if too thick.
May be prepared ahead.
Serve with crackers.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(makes own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease deep pie dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat for 1 minute on high.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fish florentine
directions: Spray a 9 x 6-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray and place fillets in pan.
Cover with a layer of spinach.
Cover with a layer of cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Drizzle with butter if desired.
Bake.

title: good-for-you maine crab cakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a mini-chopper until a wet paste. Then, blend with crabmeat in a bowl.
Using a 2-inch ice cream scoop, place a mound of crabmeat on bread crumbs.
Shape with two small spatulas and turn to coat, pressing crumbs onto cakes.
Saute in olive oil at medium-high heat for approximately 2 minutes per side or until crisp.
Yield:
four crabmeat cakes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Place oats in blender container or food processor bowl.
Cover and blend or process about 1 minute, stopping occasionally to stir. In large saucepan, fry bacon until crisp and set aside.
Pour off all (about 2 tablespoons) drippings.
Saute celery in drippings; blend in oat flour.
Gradually add water and milk.
Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Reduce heat and add reserved bacon, corn and mustard.
Continue cooking over low heat about 5 minutes or until heated through. Remove from heat, add cheese, mixing until well blended.

title: basic holiday butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and mix until thoroughly blended.
Shape and bake dough. Chill overnight.
Roll and cut into shapes for holiday cookies.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Melt Velveeta.
Combine hamburger, Velveeta, chili and chili powder. Simmer until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seafood-macaroni salad
directions: Chop crabmeat and shrimp.
Toss with macaroni, cheese, celery, green pepper and onions.
Blend remaining ingredients and toss with shrimp mixture.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, stir salad.
If desired, serve in lettuce-lined bowl and top with green pepper rings.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
You may substitute 3 bananas for the strawberries.

title: p.b. kiss cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter or margarine, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges start to brown, about 8 minutes.
Remove from pan and push Hershey Kiss in middle.
Let cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soups and water.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place raw chicken pieces on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Prepare bread for dressing, crumbling both into large bowl. Cook onions and celery in 1 cup of water on low heat until done. Add to crumbs and seasonings; add broth or milk to make a moist dressing.
Pour into a greased pan and cook at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown, or stuff in turkey cavity and bake the last hour of completed time allowed for turkey.

title: frozen fruit medley
directions: Puree pineapple juice, bananas and strawberries.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into ice cream freezer and make as you would ice cream.
No fat.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Place in quart jars.
Bring vinegar, salt and water to a hard boil.
Pour over beans in jars and seal.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop lettuce; break cauliflower into flowerets.
Fry bacon crisp and drain on paper towel.
Break into bits.
Dice onion. Mix all ingredients together and cool.
This salad will last for days in a tightly sealed bowl in refrigerator.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix in mayo well.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine vermicelli, Accent, seasoned salt, lemon juice and oil.
Mix and marinate overnight. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together, chill and serve.
Will keep 2 or 3 days, covered, in the refrigerator.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry meat and onions together in pan.
Drain.
Mix with next 3 ingredients.
The precise amounts of first three ingredients can be changed according to taste.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with tater tots.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: mother's lemon chess pie(pearl bassett)
directions: To 2 cups of sugar, add 1 tablespoon flour, 1 tablespoon cornmeal and mix together.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add butter, milk and lemon juice and mix until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake slowly at 350° in oven for approximately 35 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake mix using the package directions for a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour kahlua over the hot brownies or cake.
Let stand until cool.
Cut into bars-squares.
Prepare the mousse mix using the package directions.
Crush the candy in a large sealable plastic food storage bag with a rolling pin.
Layer the brownies or cake, mousse, whipped topping and candy 1/2 at at time in a large deep serving dish.
Chill, covered, for 8 to 12 hours.

title: baked apples
directions: Scoop out the apple cores.
Mix cinnamon with sweetener and sprinkle into the apple cores.
Sprinkle with Molly McButter. Place apples upright in small baking dish and pour the water or diet soda over them.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes in conventional oven.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip until well mixed.
Pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate overnight.
This pie also freezes well.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate until needed. Makes about 1 cup.

title: sopa de ajo(garlic soup; spain)
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, warm the olive oil over low heat and add the garlic.
Stirring frequently, cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until the garlic is soft, but not brown.
Stir in the crumbled bread and increase the heat to moderate and cook until the bread is golden.
Take care not to let it burn.
Stir in the paprika, then the water, cayenne pepper and salt and bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
With a large wooden spoon, beat the soup until the bread is pulverized.
Slowly pour in the beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Simmer for a few seconds. (Do not let the soup come near a boil or it will curdle.)
Taste for seasoning.
This will be a highly seasoned soup.
Add more cayenne pepper or salt if it seems too bland.
Serve at once, garnished with parsley.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as cake.
Add 3 large or 4 small bananas, mashed one at a time and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan or loaf pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir a moderate amount into egg yolks.
Immediately return to heat.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour into cooked shell. Spread meringue on top of pie. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: cherry fruit dessert
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and oleo until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over crumbs.
Mix sour cream and egg.
Pour over top of pie filling.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients. Toss and cover.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: dill sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours. Serve with vegetables.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks and mash them, then add remaining ingredients.
Refill the egg whites and sprinkle with a little paprika on top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In a 2 quart pot, combine soup, water, and basil.
Heat to boiling.
Add uncooked pasta.
Cook to almost done.
Add chicken and frozen vegetables.
Cook until vegetables and pasta are tender.
Top with American cheese.

title: egg noodles and tuna
directions: Boil 2 quarts of water in pan.
After water boils add 1 package egg noodles.
Boil for 7 to 10 minutes.
Strain noodles, add cream of mushroom soup.
Add tuna, butter and mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Enjoy.

title: no fool pie
directions: Melt butter in pie pan.
Mix dry ingredients and pour into pan.
Add any kind of fruit and bake at 350° until brown.

title: blue cheese dip and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, salt and pepper to taste, and refrigerate for 4 hours and serve.
To use as a salad dressing, just add milk.

title: deerfield marlborough pie(by:  harriet beecher stowe)
directions: Stir butter into hot applesauce.
Add sugar and salt.
Cool. Add lemon juice and rind to eggs slightly beaten.
Stir into sauce.
Blend well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 275° and bake for another hour.
Pie should be golden brown.

title: pumpkin and cream cheese roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (375°).
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper.
Grease and flour the wax paper.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg and salt onto wax paper.

title: crush punch
directions: Mix together and freeze in gallon jug.
Thaw out the punch 2 or 3 hours before the shower.
Place 1 gallon in punch bowl and add 1 quart ginger ale.
Makes slushy punch.

title: swedish orange cake
directions: Bake in moderate oven (350°).
When done, remove from oven and take 1/2 cup powdered sugar and the juice of one orange.
Mix well and slowly pour over cake after removing from oven.

title: lena rohrer's (my mama) pineapple pie(for 2 pies)
directions: Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites for topping.

title: prize butter bars
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and beat on low speed until fine particles form.
Reserve 1 cup. Press remaining crumbs in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, butter and brown sugar.
Spread over bottom layer as evenly as possible.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili for a crowd
directions: Brown meat, onions and green peppers.
Drain off grease.
In a large pot, add the meat and all the rest of the ingredients, making sure to rinse pinto and kidney beans before adding to chili.
Let simmer on low for 1 hour.
Check seasonings for flavor, adding any to suit your taste.
Let simmer 1 hour more.
The longer it simmers on low, the better the flavor.
More water must be added when reheating.
It's great with shredded Cheddar cheese on top. Freezes well.

title: ground beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Stir soups, olives, cheese and meat mixture into cooked noodles.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 18 to 20 people.
Freezes well.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese well.
Add sour cream and beat until smooth, then add sugar and vanilla, blending well.
Beat in eggs until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 8 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off and allow cake to remain in oven for another hour.
Remove cake from oven; cool.
Topping the cake with any flavor fruit pie filling after it is cool, gives height to the cake.

title: apple cake
directions: With electric mixer, beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients, then apples, raisins and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Use a well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.)
Good with ice cream!
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Place Shake 'N Bake, oregano and garlic powder in bag.
Coat and bake chicken as directed on package.
Heat spaghetti sauce. Pour over chicken just before serving.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes covered until tender, 30 minutes.
Do not overcook; drain and cool.
Peel and cut into cubes with salt, pepper, onions, radishes, celery seed and parsley.
Saute bacon in skillet over low heat until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon. Remove bacon and add to potatoes.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon of bacon fat; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add vinegar and 1/2 cup water. Stir in sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stirring, toss potato mixture until combined.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add milk and yeast; mix well.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead lightly, then roll out and cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter to make Parker House rolls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Let rise to double in bulk, then bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat together cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk (I use electric mixer).
Add instant vanilla pudding and milk.
Beat all together, chill 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip to pudding mixture.
Layer cookies, bananas, and pudding mixture, over and over.
Then add 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip for topping.
Crumble vanilla wafers on top.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift and blend together sugar and cocoa in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pour in milk.
Place butter on top.
Heat in microwave on Full power for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir well to mix ingredients.

title: rum pie
directions: In top part of double boiler, combine sugar, flour, egg and light cream.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly for 5 minutes, until very thick.
Add rum and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in whipped cream; put in graham cracker crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter tandy-cake
directions: Grease and flour a jelly roll pan.
Cream eggs and sugar; add milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While hot, spread with peanut butter; cool. Melt chocolate bar and pour over cake.

title: strawberry luscious
directions: Dissolve gelatin
in
boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries with
juice,
undrained
pineapple	and bananas, which have been mashed and	whipped.
Pour	half of mixture into 8 x 12-inch pan. Chill
until set.
Spread sour cream over top of congealed layer. Cover
with
remaining gelatin.
Chill until firm.	Decorate top if desired.

title: mrs. bowden's peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice peaches and mix with 3/4 cup sugar.
Let stand 2 hours.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; mix with 1 cup of sugar.
Stir in milk and add almond extract.
Melt the butter in a deep baking dish and pour the batter over it.
Do not stir.
Pour the peaches over the top of the batter to form a layer.
Bake in a moderate (350°) oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
If you use a glass baking dish, bake at 325°. Check it, as you do not want the juices to caramelize.

title: best banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Blend in sour milk and egg yolks.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend with milk mixture.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Stir.
Beat in egg whites.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Pour into floured and greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Best when frosted with cream cheese or vanilla icing.

title: orange-mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Cool.
Add orange juice and melt. Stir until syrupy, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 7 x 12-inch pan and chill.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: corn on the cob("barbecue" style)
directions: Soak corn in husks in cool water for about 4 hours.
By standing corn on end
(vertically)
and
wedging
tightly in a bucket you can keep them covered with water.

title: lemon rice and peas
directions: Place water and rice in a saucepan; cook according to package directions.
Set aside.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut a big slit in pork chop.
Fill with stuffing.
Place in glass pan.
Top pork chops with garlic powder, onion salt, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in oven and lightly brown.
Make beef or chicken bouillon (or mixture of both) highly concentrated.
Pour over chops.
Keep basting.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spinach linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Discard the tough ribs and stems from the spinach, then wash it thoroughly.
Fill the small pan with salted water and bring to a boil.
Add the spinach and simmer until tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water and drain again.
Squeeze to remove all excess water.
Puree spinach in a food processor or chop finely.
Sift the flour onto a work surface in a mound; with your fingers, make a well in the center.
Add the eggs to the well, followed by the oil, salt and spinach.
Mix together with your fingertips.
Gradually mix in the flour from the sides to make a firm dough.
If sticky, add more flour.
Press the dough together into a ball.
Knead, roll out and cut the dough using the pasta machine, ending with the rollers at the narrowest setting and using the narrower of the machine's cutters.
Or knead, roll out and cut the dough by hand, rolling it to the thickness of a postcard and cutting it into 1/8-inch wide strips.
Toss the linguine gently with a little flour or fine cornmeal, then coil it loosely in bundles or leave it flat and spread out on a floured dish towel. Let dry 1 to 2 hours.
Scrub the clams under cold running water. Put clams in casserole or large saucepan.
Finely chop onion and add to casserole with the wine.
Cover and cook over high heat, shaking occasionally, until the shells open, 5 to 8 minutes. Discard any unopened clams.
Put clams in a bowl.
Set aside to cool slightly.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Combine milk, water and butter in saucepan. Heat until warm. Add to 2 c. flour, sugar, salt and yeast; beat. Gradually add rest of flour; turn out on flour-covered board. Knead. Place in greased bowl, put down into pan of hot water. Let rise 15 minutes. Knead. Shape into rolls and put into greased pans. Cover and let rise 15 minutes. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat heavy cream; fold into other mixture.
Line a spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake biscuits in sugar and cinnamon to coat.
Put in greased bundt pan.
Pour remaining sugar over biscuits.
Melt 1 stick of butter, 3/4 c. sugar and 2 tsp. vanilla.
Pour over biscuits and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut out stem end of tomatoes and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Mix salt, pepper and cornmeal in a dish.
Coat both sides of tomatoes with mixture.
Heat the butter in a skillet.
Add tomatoes and brown on both sides.
Cook until tender.

title: mike's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes which have been peeled and cut in 1/2-inch strips the length of potato or 1/2-inch rounds.
Drain and set aside (don't overcook).
Combine sugar, Karo and water.
Bring to light boil.
Add butter and potatoes.
Cook on simmer until done. Be sure you don't overcook.

title: white trash
directions: In a large bowl, melt almond bark.
Stir until well coated the pretzels, coconut, almonds, peanuts and cereal.
Spread evenly in jelly roll pan.
Cool.
Turn onto breadboard and cut into random pieces.

title: lou's t. v. surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Open T. V. dinner box.
Remove tray. Remove foil from tray.
Place dinner in oven.
Bake 35 minutes. Remove T. V. dinner from oven with oven mitt.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Enjoy!

title: quick fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Into a very large bowl, break into pieces, the Hershey candy bar, chocolate chips and German chocolate.
Pour boiling syrup over broken chocolate pieces.
Stir well.
When mixed, add marshmallow cream.
Stir until well mixed.
Push into 9 x 13-inch pans, well-greased.
When cold, cut into pieces.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, spoon crushed pineapple over cake.
Make vanilla pudding according to directions.
Pour over pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip (9 ounces or so) and top with flaked coconut.

title: candied pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place pecans in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Toast in oven for 5 minutes, or until golden brown.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Stir in corn syrup and 1/4 cup sugar, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Pour syrup over pecans, stirring constantly to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring several times.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Toss to coat evenly.
Immediately spread out on greased baking sheet to cool. Quickly separate into individual pecans.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Put paper liners in muffin tin.
Put vanilla wafers in paper. Cream the ingredients together (except filling).
Fill liners 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.
Top with cherry, blueberry or lemon pie filling.

title: christmas drops
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs in large bowl until fluffy. Stir in sour cream.
Add next 5 sifted dry ingredients; mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients except cherry halves.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with cherry half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: crazy-wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil, vinegar and vanilla. Pour water over all, then stir with fork.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: best swiss steak
directions: Rub steak with side of garlic.
Chop and reserve garlic. Pound flour, salt and pepper into the steak.
Melt shortening; brown steak on both sides.
Top steak with onion slices, tomatoes, carrots, celery, green pepper and chopped garlic.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: cocoa-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and margarine.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take off heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop onto wax paper while hot.
Let cool.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on package.
Mix with soup and cheeses.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs and top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet supper
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Set aside. Heat skillet to 350°. Add ground beef, onion and pepper. Cook until meat is brown and vegetables are tender. Drain well. Spread meat and vegetables mixture evenly in skillet. Place cooked noodles in center. Spoon tomato sauce and grated cheese on top of mixture. Serves 4 to 6.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Grease a large baking
dish
and line bottom with dried beef. Place chicken on top.
Mix	sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken
and
sprinkle
with
paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with wild, long grain rice.

title: briscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast the almonds for a few minutes until they are golden.
Let cool, chop.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Cream butter, add sugar and beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in the eggs, add mandarin peel, Contreau and cinnamon. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat flour mixture in with butter mixture.
Stir in chopped almonds.

title: torta rustica
directions: Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with 2/3 of the Sour Cream Pastry.
With half the Prosciutto, make a layer on the bottom of the pastry shell, overlapping slices, if necessary.

title: chicken artichoke salad
directions: Prepare chicken Rice-A-Roni and let cool.
Add black olives, celery, green onions, artichoke hearts and pimentos.
Stir together the marinade from the artichokes and mayonnaise.
Stir into other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add chicken or turkey, if desired.
Chill overnight.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and mix with all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 6 hours. Before serving, add 1 cup of cooked macaroni and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes
in microwave about 5 minutes per potato. Cut in half lengthwise.
Spoon out inside of potato into bowl. Mix with sour cream and margarine; add grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into potato skins.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: creole dinner
directions: Cut steak into thin strips and place over oil.
Salt and pepper.
Add thinly sliced onions, carrots and potatoes.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add soup and water.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft.
They will puff during baking, flatten upon cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute.
Remove to wire; cool.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and green chilies in butter; add mushroom soup, chicken soup, milk and chicken.
Pour over crushed Doritos and add Cheddar or Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: triple casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, olive oil, onion and sauces for dressing. Cook the beans and peas separately as directed on package; drain. Marinate all in dressing.
Top with the grated eggs.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In 2-quart casserole, place confectioners sugar.
Place cream cheese, butter and vanilla over top.
Microwave at High for 1 minute, just until ingredients can be beaten together.
Remove, beat and frost the cake.

title: fruit roll-ups
directions: Puree fruit in blender to make 2 1/2 to 3 cups. Pour into jelly roll pan lined with Saran Wrap.
Place in oven for 8 hours on lowest temperature.
Watch carefully as it nears the end of the 8 hours; roll-ups should still be a bit tender and rollable.
Cut and roll up, leaving Saran Wrap on.

title: coffee cinnamon rolls
directions: Dip each biscuit into melted oleo and then roll each piece in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Arrange the biscuits in an angel food pan.
After each layer of biscuits, sprinkle on chopped nuts. Repeat until all biscuits are gone.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
You may use frozen dinner rolls instead of the biscuits, but allow them to rise before baking.

title: cheesy pudding(good with steak; takes the place of bread)
directions: Mix cheese and butter.
Spread on bread; cut each slice in 3 strips.
Arrange in a 2-quart greased casserole.
Beat the eggs with the milk, salt and dry mustard; pour over bread.
Let this sit overnight in refrigerator.
Take out an hour before baking. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Will be brown on top.
Serve immediately, or it will fall.

title: honey nuts
directions: Sift sugar and spices three times.
Spread half the mixture in 1/4-inch layer on a baking sheet.
Beat egg white, honey and salt together until mixed thoroughly.
Add nut halves; stir until coated well.
Place nuts on sugar mixture one at a time; cover with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cool and store in covered jar.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a big bowl, add eggs and oil, stir until moistened.
Do not beat with a mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Mix and fold in bananas.
Spoon into 3 well-greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool.

title: quick chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine above ingredients (except chicken) with 8 cups water. Add 1 carrot diced in a Dutch oven or soup pot.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Discard bay leaf. Stir in 3 cups cooked chicken; simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken, water and chicken bouillon in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
When chicken is cooked, remove from pan and add other ingredients.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Bake uncovered for another 30 minutes.
If rice mixture becomes dry, add additional water.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Mix well. Stir in 1 1/2 cups water gradually.

Mix in slightly beaten egg yolks, butter and lemonade. Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly. Cook to lukewarm. Spread in pie shell. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until stiff peaks form. Pour over filling. Seal to edge. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: pork chops continental
directions: Brown chops in their own fat in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Season.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Add broccoli to 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover and cook until almost tender.
Drain.
Mix with onion, pepper and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch pie plate. Mix milk, Bisquick, eggs and salt in a mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth, about 1 minute, with mixer.
Pour over mixture in pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cheese and 1/2 cup sour cream; stir constantly over low heat until cheese melts. Add cooked chicken and chilies to cheese mixture, stirring until heated through. Heat tortilla chips on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes. Arrange half the tortilla chips on a serving platter and top with half the chicken mixture.
Repeat layering with remaining chips and chicken mixture.
Sprinkle lettuce and tomato on top. Garnish nachos with sour cream, guacamole and salsa. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on cake box.
Add coconut and flavoring.

Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan by directions on box. While cake is baking, mix evaporated milk, powdered sugar, vanilla and coconut flavoring plus enough water to make a scant 2 cups of the ingredients.
(I use 3/4 cup or more of water.)
After cake is done and is still warm, pierce the top with a toothpick and pour the mixture over cake.
Cool in the refrigerate overnight.
Spread top with whipped topping and sprinkle with 1 package of frozen coconut (thawed).
Keep refrigerated.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter and vanilla. When creamy, add powdered sugar and continue to blend. If the icing is too dry, add 1 tablespoon of milk at a time; continue to blend until it reaches desired consistency. Frost cake, then sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans or walnuts (chopped).

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together until well mixed.
Roll into 1-inch balls or layer, if desired.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: my mother lillie's spinach souffle
directions: Melt butter; add flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg, then add milk.
Stir until well blended.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add cheese and spinach; cook until cheese is melted.
Cool; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff; in another bowl, beat yolks.
Add yolks to cheese and spinach mixture.
Fold in whites.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and jello with water in pan; cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Cool until lukewarm.
Blend in cream cheese with low speed of electric mixer.
Put into refrigerator until partially set.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions. Fold into jello mixture; add nuts.
Pour mixture into 9 x 12-inch dish; refrigerate until firm.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Use 11 egg yolks and 1 whole egg.
Mix with water and vinegar. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out thin and cut in strips.
Let dry.
Makes 3 (1/2 pound) bags.
(You can use egg whites for pies or make angel food cakes with them.)

title: squash cakes
directions: Mix all together, except cheese, and fry in butter until brown on both sides.
Put 1/2 slice of cheese on cakes while still hot.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix lightly together the sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water for 3 to 5 minutes; reserve liquid. Saute celery and onion in butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add stock and liquid from broccoli, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add broccoli.
Put through a food mill or puree in an electric blender, if desired.
Stir egg yolks into half and half. Gradually add to soup, being careful not to boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish each serving with a sprinkle of paprika. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 3/4-inch cubes.
Brown meat in oil.
In the same pan, combine all the other ingredients except the cold water and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until the meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Blend in the cold water with cornstarch and add to the stew.
Serve over the noodles, cooked per package directions. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add the cranberry sauce.
Stir until smooth. Chill in refrigerator until just set.
Fold in nuts and celery. Return to refrigerator for 2 hours or until completely jelled.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter, sugar, vanilla and vinegar.
Let cool.
Beat eggs. Add other ingredients and mix with other mixture.
Bake in shell for 45 to 50 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large.

title: chocolate cream cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 18 muffin cups with liners.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips; set aside.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Top each with tablespoon of cream cheese mix.
Sprinkle with sugar and nuts.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until cream mix is golden.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Line an 8x8x2-inch pan with foil;
butter foil.
Combine sugar and milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Boil, stirring constantly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; beat in chocolate and marshmallows with wooden spoon.
Stir until thick;
stir in nuts and cherries.
Pour into pan;
cool until firm.
Turn out onto cutting board;
cut into 1-inch squares. Store in tighltly covered container.
Can be frozen for up to 6 months.

title: cheese casserole(baked cheese fondue)
directions: In large bowl; beat eggs, add milk, salt, pepper, mustard. In greased casserole, layer cubed, buttered bread and cheese. Pour egg mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (until golden brown and souffle-like). Serves 6 to 8.

title: cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, oatmeal, baking powder and vanilla.
Add nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Do not overbake.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble cake.
Prepare pudding mix.
Layer cake crumbs, strawberries, pineapple, pudding, whipped topping, nuts and coconut, 1/2 at a time in a large bowl.
Serves 12.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Separate dough into 16 triangles. Dip marshmallow in melted butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on wide end of triangle.
Fold corners over marshmallow and roll toward point.
Completely cover marshmallow; squeeze edges of dough to seal.
Dip point in butter; place buttered side down in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and drizzle with icing; sprinkle with nuts.

title: baked creamed chicken
directions: Mix the sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer bottom with the white chicken and layer soup mixture over.
Roll out the tube of Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of soup.
Slice margarine and pat on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: quick and easy rice casserole(serves 4)
directions: Spread rice in the bottom of a small casserole dish.
Pour in soup and mushrooms.
Don't stir.
Put the stick of butter in the center on top.
Cover and bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheeses, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Shape in a ball, then roll in nuts. Serve with party crackers of your choice.
I make two cheese balls from this recipe.

title: baked corn
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix corn, salt and eggs well.
Mix crumbs into corn.
Spread remaining crumbs on top.
Melt butter or margarine to pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let set before serving.
