title: portuguese cabbage soup
directions: Start cooking
meat in water to cover 3 days in advance and beans
days in advance with salt to taste.
Add seasonings, onion,
carrots and potatoes.
Simmer until carrots are soft and potatoes
are breaking up.
Add kielbasa or sausages cut in bite-size
chunks
and cabbage.
Cook until cabbage is tender. Serve hot.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until light; add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn onto a cake rack to cool completely.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix pudding according to package.
Layer pudding, cookie crumbs and Cool Whip.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar, butter, baking powder, vanilla, milk, and flour gradually.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes for each layer. Can use 3 or 4 pans, 8 or 9 inches.
On each layer of cake, first put holes in cake.
Add coconut milk and some coconut.
Add icing and more coconut.
Stack each layer and cover cake with remainder of icing.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, alternating bananas and wafers.
Pour pudding mix over each alternation.

title: french toast
directions: Bread -- Soak each slice and saute in butter for each slice until golden on both sides, about 1 1/2 minutes.
You can sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm, with syrup if desired.

title: fruit delight pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar and lemon juice together until thickened.
Add pineapple, peaches and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix well and pour into 2 deep graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Wash cranberries and heat
over
medium heat with sugar and 1 cup of boiling
water, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.	Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes
cups
or three pints.

title: norm mulpeter's grilled bluefish
directions: Put foil on grill; put fish, brown side down, on foil.
Cover with lemon juice and garlic powder; spread on lots of mayonnaise, chopped onion and pepper.
Put grill on high; cook with the top down for 5 minutes on high, 5 to 7 minutes on medium, until the edge of the fish gets almost black and the onion browns.
Even if you don't like fish, you'll like this!

title: chalupas
directions: In large frypan, cook onions until soft.
Add beef and cook through.
Add beans and spices to taste.
Heat tostada shells according to package directions.
Spread a layer of meat mixture on top of shell, then follow with toppings.
It's best to start with the cheese so it will melt.

title: irish creme
directions: Mix all in a blender for about 1 minute. Serve over chipped ice.
Very refreshing drink.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add water, Miracle Whip salad dressing and vanilla and mix.
Bake in 8 x 10-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: calico coleslaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving add salt and mayonnaise.
Toss lightly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: angel food pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, water and salt in saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil. Add cornstarch and cook until thickened. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cooled mixture; pour into pie shell. Beat whipped cream until soft peaks are formed, adding sugar to taste. Spread on top of pie and sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted margarine and 3 tbsp sugar.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Bake eight minutes at 400 degrees.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear the cleaned crispy lettuce into bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given. Add the sugar to the mayonnaise and spread over the top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 10 hours.
At serving time, garnish with additional bacon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery in butter.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma parkes chow chow
directions: Combine vegetables. Sprinkle with salt. Let stand for 4 to 6 hours. Drain and rinse well. Combine vinegar, sugar and pickling spice. Simmer 30 minutes to flavor vinegar. Add vegetables. Simmer 10 minutes. Bring to boil. Pack boiling hot into Ball jars. Great with peas in the winter months.

title: geneva's chicken casserole
directions: Mix cornbread mix, butter and water.
Place 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix onions, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour this over the cornbread mix in the dish.
Spread 2 1/2 cups cooked chicken over this mixture.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon in plastic bag. Cut biscuits into pieces and shake in bag until well coated. Place pieces in greased Bundt pan.

title: macaroni surprise
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain off grease.
Place in large salad bowl.
Add macaroni; mix well.
Then add eggs.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Mix well.
Serve with your favorite salad dressing.

title: maryland crab cakes with corn relish
directions: If using fresh crabmeat, pick over with your fingers, discarding any cartilage or shell.
Place in bowl.
Trim and discard the bread crusts.
Put bread in food processor and work to form crumbs.
Strip parsley and dill leaves fro stems.
Coarsely chop leaves.
Add mayonnaise, herbs and bread crumbs to the crabmeat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir crab mixture gently with wooden spoon until ingredients are combined.
Lightly beat eggs; add to crab cake mixture and stir to combine.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in blender.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Mix brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream.

title: tortellini pasta salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to directions on package.
Drain; toss with oil (small amount).
Let cool.
Mix with vegetables and dressing at least 2 hours before serving and then chill.

title: dummy cake or crazy cake
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of greased pan; top with cake mix, coconut and pecans.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together.
Combine with remaining ingredients.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix in a large bowl the oats, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts. Bring to a boil the margarine, milk and sugar. Pour over mixture. Put on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick in double boiler. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Blend with mixer or in blender until all lumps are gone and it is very creamy.
Pour into two pie shells. Use Cool Whip as topping.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Dissolve 1/4 cup sugar in 1/4 cup warm water.
Sprinkle 1 package yeast in this mixture.
In another bowl, mix 2 tablespoons shortening, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 2 cups warm water. Add yeast mixture to this and add enough plain flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl, let rise overnight or until it rises good.

title: diet chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken, place in large skillet.
Pour catsup over chicken.
Add cola to pan.
Cook over low heat 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Baste occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Then sift flour, cinnamon, ginger and salt; mix well.
Add soda; mix well.
Put in flat pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: noodles with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; saute in oil over medium heat until golden.
Drain clam liquid into onion mixture.
Stir in wine.
Simmer about 5 minutes over medium heat. Stir in clams, parsley, pepper and butter.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour clam sauce over hot, cooked pasta noodles.
Garnish with watercress sprigs.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: creamy holiday eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites in large bowl until soft peaks form.
Add yolks and honey; beat well.
Stir in milk and extracts.
Chill. Just before serving, fold in whipped cream.
Pour into punch bowl; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: sausage ryes(hanky pankys)
directions: Fry beef and sausage until brown; drain grease.
Slice cheese; cut up and mix into meat until well blended.
Spoon onto ryes, 1 tablespoon each.
Bake in oven for 8 to 10 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Pour olive oil in heavy saucepan. Stir in celery, onion and green pepper. Cook until tender. Add garlic and pepper to taste. In a bowl, mix together the tomato sauce, water and whole tomatoes.
Cut shrimp into 1/2-inch pieces and blend into tomato mixture. Add to the onion, green pepper and celery mixture.
Cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours or place in slow cooker.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pork chops 'n' rice
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Brown meat on both sides in oil.
Cover bottom of shallow baking dish with rice.
Place chops and onions on top.
Add water, sugar and seasonings to drippings in skillet.
Stir and pour over chops.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake uncovered in a moderate oven (325°) about 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot  fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly!
Cook over medium heat until thickens (approximately 8 minutes).

title: dieters "delite" peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat egg white until bubbly.
Add cream of tartar, beat until it makes peaks.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Add peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.
(18 calories each; NO cholesterol)

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling in a bowl, then pour into floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Pour cake mix over pineapple and cherry mixture.
Sprinkle the nuts and coconut over all of the cake. Cut the butter into squares and place over cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill butter with vegetables
directions: Melt butter. Add lemon juice and dill weed. Add 1/2 cup sauce to each of the "hot" vegetables.
Mix well and serve.

title: german salad
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop fine the green pepper and onion.
Boil together the wet ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: county fair chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk, then coat with cheese mixture.
Place in 9 x 11 greased baking dish.
Pour butter over top and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour only.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: copper pennies
directions: Prepare first three ingredients.

title: orange pork chops(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a large
skillet over medium heat, brown chops in margarine.
Drain oranges, reserving syrup; set fruit aside.
In a small bowl, combine syrup, brown sugar, catsup, vinegar, salt, mustard, cinnamon and cloves.
Pour over chops.
Cover and simmer over low heat for
45 minutes or until pork is tender.
Add orange segments during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Remove cloves before serving.

title: kimona egg sandwich filling("egg goo")
directions: Blend the sugar, flour, butter and milk in double boiler. Then beat in the raw egg.
Use a whisk to keep from sticking. Cook until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Cool.
Fold in the cream cheese, then add the diced, hard-boiled eggs.
Add onions or chives and chopped pimento.
Mix well.
Keep chilled.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bring to boil, then set pan in cold water. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Then add 1 pint of hulled strawberries, saving some for garnish.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Dream Whip.
Garnish with remaining strawberries.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: In large pot, bring water to boil with remaining ingredients. Simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain and rinse off grease.
Place crescent rolls in large ungreased pizza pan with the points facing the center of the pan.
Pinch together to make the crust.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach.
Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with French bread or crackers.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Saute onions and pepper in small amount of margarine.
Add ground beef and brown slightly.
Add soup and water; simmer until beef is done and sauce has thickened.
Serve over buns.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil
chicken
and
bone.
Use
cups
broth and cook frozen vegetables, onion, celery and potatoes.
When done, add chicken and cream of chicken soup.
Season to taste; mix well. Put
in baking
dish.
Open
small can of biscuits.
Cut into quarters and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: The night before:
Melt butter, stir in brown sugar and syrup.
Spread in the bottom of a 9-inch by 13-inch baking pan. Arrange apple slices over top.
Place bread slices over top of apples.
Beat eggs until light.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour evenly over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, for about 40 minutes until bread is golden brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Melt butter, put cabbage and onion in pan; cook till tender. Cook and drain 2 c. noodles; add cabbage and onion.

title: walnut applesauce cake
directions: Add soda to cake mix.
Substitute applesauce for liquid using 1/4 cup more applesauce than the liquid called for on package. Mix cake as package directs, adding the extra 1/4 cup applesauce to first mixing.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake as directed on package.

title: california rotelle salad
directions: Cook rotelle and vegetables until done.
Drain both.
Combine rotelle and vegetables.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese and salad dressing.
Sprinkle on desired amount of Parmesan cheese.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan over medium heat; stir constantly until mixture is thick, like caramel.
Be careful; this will burn very easily.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, then nuts. Stir until all nuts are coated well.
Mixture will become "grainy" like dried sugar.
Turn out on cookie sheet or pizza pan to dry.
Make sure completely dry.
Store in a dry place in jars or airtight containers.
Keeps 3 to 4 months.
Do not freeze or refrigerate.
Great for Christmas.

title: cherry cider
directions: Combine apple cider and cinnamon stick in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Serve beverage hot.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: apricot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into rolls or balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned vanilla ice cream(4 quarts)
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Stir in whole milk.
Stir over medium heat until mixture begins to simmer.
Simmer 1 minute over low heat; set aside.

title: german chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and butter.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add chocolate, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and top with Coconut Pecan Topping. Chill and cut into squares.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch Teflon pan or foil-lined pan with graham crackers.
Boil the butter, brown sugar and nuts 3 minutes in saucepan.
Pour evenly over graham crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven off and place chocolate chips or Hershey bars on top of cookies; return to oven until chocolate melts. Spread it.
Sprinkle with jimmies.
(Note:
cookies should be broken apart while warm so they don't break.)

title: strawberry delight
directions: Layer #1:
Melt margarine.
Add flour and nuts.
Press in bottom of baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: rice milanese
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion in a large skillet.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth to the skillet.
Add the 1 cup rice.
Stir the rice mixture and when it thickens, add a little more broth. Continue slowly adding broth until it is all used up.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: brown rice
directions: Fry bacon, onion and green pepper together.
Add rice, soy sauce and water.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Soften corn tortillas in heavy skillet with oil.
Fill with cheese and finely chopped onion.
Roll and place seam side down in casserole dish.
Cover with chili; add more cheese.
Heat and serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Put in a large airtight container and label.
Makes 17 cups of hot chocolate mix.
Add 3 tablespoons of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and place in gallon jar.
Add vinegar, salt, pickling spice and alum.
Add cold water to fill jar.
Place lid on jar and let stand 3 to 4 weeks.
Drain pickles; rinse and slice thinly into a large bowl.
Cucumbers will be soft at this time but will become crisp later.
Add sugar and water and let stand, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved.
Put in plastic or glass containers and place in refrigerator.
Will keep for one year.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar and salt in double boiler.
Pour scalded milk over this mixture.
Cook over boiling water until mixture thickens, stirring almost constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add hot mixture very slowly to beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return to double boiler and cook 2 minutes.
Let cool and add vanilla.
Put alternate layers of vanilla wafers, banana slices and pudding mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole, having top layer pudding.
Garnish with banana slices and whole vanilla wafers.
Let cool, then chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: bean bake
directions: Put meat and onion in a large skillet and heat, but don't brown.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Place in bottom of casserole dish. (Save chicken broth.)
Cut up onion and place on top of chicken. Mix soups and milk.
Heat mixture and pour on chicken and onion. Put stuffing on top of soup mixture.
Pour in chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: basic shortbread dough
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and blend. Divide dough into 4 balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets, 2 balls on each of 2 sheets.
Prick with fork.
Sprinkle with colored sugar; pat into dough.
Score with knife into 6 wedges.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes.
While warm, cut wedges through and cool on wire racks.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and
bake at 425° until bread is a light gold.

title: strawberry delight(fat free)
directions: Tear cake into small pieces, spread 1/2 of cake into bottom of cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix cream cheese, milk, Dream Whip and vanilla.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture over cake.
Repeat cake, then cream cheese mixture.
Add strawberries to glaze.
Pour over cake. Let sit overnight.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup. Pat remaining mixture lightly into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Spread contents of soup over chicken breasts. Bake in oven, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°, depending upon size of chicken breasts.

title: whole wheat buns
directions: Let raise once and shape into buns.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse angel food cake
directions: Combine chips, sugar and water in a double boiler.
Cook until melted.
Beat egg yolk for 1 minute; add to chocolate mixture and beat 3 minutes more.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Fold in 1 3/4 cups whipped cream.
Layer bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan with cake.
Spread half the chocolate filling on cake layer. Repeat layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top cake with whipped cream and grated chocolate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, cook ham 5 minutes.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Blend in flour and brown slowly stirring often.
Stir in tomatoes, water and parsley.
Bring to a boil and add rice, Worcestershire, salt, thyme and pepper.
Return to boil.
Reduce and simmer covered 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: sweet and sour spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles. Drain and cool. Add vegetables and eggs.

title: apple-nut muffins
directions: Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with cups.
In bowl, beat egg with juice, oil and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and apple.
Fill cups.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: merry berry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in water.
Add frozen raspberries and lemon juice, stirring until thawed.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch and 6 x 6-inch Pyrex dishes and refrigerate until firm.
Cover with sour cream.
Dissolve cherry gelatin in water and add remaining ingredients.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over sour cream.
Chill thoroughly.

title: hodge podge
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Mix in all ingredients, except rice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour over rice, if desired.

title: beef barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Place biscuits in ungreased muffin cups.
Press dough to cover bottom and sides of cup.
Spoon hot meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger
meat
and
onions
in	pan.
Add other ingredients and
simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
(Pour water off mushrooms but leave water in tomatoes.)

title: cherry chocolate dessert
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cake mix and pie filling.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot mulled wine
directions: Add to syrup.
While heating, dilute with 2 to 4 cups water. Add one large bottle (1/2 gallon size) red wine.

title: crackling bread
directions: Cracklings are the pieces of meat remaining after the lard has been rendered from the pork.
Mix and sift together the dry ingredients.
Add the milk.
Stir in the cracklings.
Form into oblong cakes and place in greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple salsa
directions: Sprinkle the pineapple with lime juice, ginger and honey.
Add peppers.
Use this with sausage dishes, liver pate and fried chicken livers.
Good for parties.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend soup and milk; heat thoroughly.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until melted.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
If desired, top with toasted, slivered almonds.
Bake uncovered in 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned apple crescents
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Toss with apples and lemon juice.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick and cut into 12 (7-inch) circles.
Place 1/2 cup filling on one half of each circle.
Fold dough over filling to form crescent.
Seal edges with fork.
Cut slits in top.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 20 minutes.
When cool, wrap crescents individually and freeze.
Makes 12 crescents.

title: apple raisin bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, soak cereal in milk for 5 minutes.
Stir in Promise, honey, apple, raisins, egg and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
With a rubber spatula, fold flour into apple bran mixture, just enough to moisten.
Do not over mix. Evenly distribute among muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: mama's good soup
directions: Bacon must be fried first.
Leave bacon grease.
Throw other meat in and brown it on the outside a little.
Pour about 2 quarts of water over the meat and bring to a boil.
In a separate skillet, make a small rue of 4 tablespoons of oil and 2 tablespoons of flour.
Brown rue and drop into boiling meat and water.
Add vegetables, onion, tomato sauce, and tomatoes.
Cook slow for about 30 minutes.

title: spicy grilled catfish fillets
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, stir well, cover and chill. Combine next 3 ingredients, rub on both sides of fish.
Place fish in wire grill basket coated with cooking spray.
Grill about 5 to 7 minutes on each side, depending on thickness of fish.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of sauce over each fillet, garnish with lemon wedge. Yields 4 servings.

title: stuffed edam cheese
directions: Take one-inch off top of Edam cheese.
Scoop out cheese, leaving red shell.
Chill shell and let cheese soften.
Beat cheese and add the rest of the ingredients.
Fill shell and refrigerate, mounding high.
Serve on party rye.
Keeps several days.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Then add 1 cup of something you like, such as raisins, dates, chopped nuts, etc. (She used 1 cup chunky applesauce with 1 cup of raisins.)

title: chicken scampi
directions: In a 2-quart dish, microwave oil or margarine for 1 minute. Add chicken and all other ingredients.
Cover and microwave another 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: anniversary pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour in bundt or angel food cake pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done. Let cool in pan covered with foil. Makes own frosting.

title: cheese broccoli bake
directions: Remove tough part of broccoli stalks.
Cut fresh broccoli lengthwise into uniform spears.
Cut off buds and set aside.
Cut remaining broccoli into 1-inch pieces.
In medium covered saucepan, cook the stalk pieces of broccoli in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes, or just until tender.
Add broccoli buds the last 5 minutes of cooking.
(Cook frozen broccoli according to package; drain well.)

title: south of the border
directions: Brown and drain sausage, onion and green pepper.
Mix all other remaining ingredients.
Add to sausage mixture.
Simmer in skillet approximately 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Combine juice from peaches, cinnamon sticks, cloves and vinegar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add peach halves.
Can be served warm or chilled.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Combine sour cream and pepperoni.
Store in refrigerator, covered, for 2 days.
Serve in hollowed loaf brown bread with bread pieces.

title: devilish deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Mash yolks with fork.
Blend in relish, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper. Refill egg whites with mixture.
Cover.
Chill to blend flavors. Garnish top of eggs with chopped parsley or paprika.
Makes 12 halves.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Combine butter and lemon juice. Dip chicken breasts in this then dip in combined spaghetti sauce mix and stuffing mix.
Place chicken skin side up in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish or pan. Pour half and half cream around and between chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese and bake 2 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fried rice
directions: Take the butter and Worcestershire and place in electric skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Fry rice in this mixture. Add bacon.
Be creative; may add water chestnuts, mushrooms, bean sprouts, celery, etc.

title: french cinnamon toast
directions: Mix the contents from inside the eggs with the other ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
After well mixed, dip the slices of bread in mixture coating both sides.
Place bread in a skillet with melted butter.
Fry until done, approximately 1 minute each side.
For best taste, serve with maple syrup (Bob White).

title: broccoli ham and swiss rolls
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour; cook and stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli, sour cream, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Using sharp knife, remove 1/2-inch slice from top of each roll; set aside.
Remove bread from inside of rolls, leaving about 1/2-inch shell.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of hot broccoli mixture into each roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet or boiler pan. Top each with 1 slice ham, 1 slice tomato and 1 slice cheese. Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Place top of roll on each sandwich.
Yields 4 sandwiches.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together and drain.
Add the can of chicken soup, the sour cream and all of the seasons.
Mix well. Layer the stuffing mix and the squash mix in casserole dish (bottom stuffing mix, squash mix, etc.).
Melt the butter or margarine and pour over top of mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: ted's bread pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Boil water, sugar, butter and flour for 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon of lemon flavoring and a little nutmeg.
Pour over baked pudding.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Soak chestnuts in vinegar, soy sauce and liquid from can. Soak several hours.
Drain.
Rub each strip of bacon with brown sugar.
Cut each strip into thirds. Wrap each chestnut with a piece of bacon, sugar side in.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Use a baking rack to prevent sticking and allow grease to drain.)

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat soup, chilies, sour cream and white chicken until smooth. Place one spoonful of soup mixture, cheese and onion onto tortilla.
Roll up tortilla and place into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining soup mixture over rolled up tortillas.
Top with cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer until stew thickens. Serve over vegetables.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain well.
Cook onion and green peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in cream of chicken soup, mushrooms, pimento, skim milk and basil. Lay half the noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with half the soup mixture, cottage cheese, chicken, American cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with remaining American cheese and Parmesan cheese; bake another 2 minutes, or until cheeses are melted.
Makes 10 servings.

title: butterscotch overnight cookies
directions: Mix at night and make into a roll.
Keep in refrigerator.
In the morning, slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Heat vinegar in a double boiler.
Beat eggs; add sugar and salt.
Stir in hot vinegar.
Add butter and cook until thick. Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: yogurt dinner rolls
directions: In a saucepan, heat together yogurt, margarine, water and sugar until margarine is melted.
Set aside and let cool to lukewarm.
In a large bowl, combine yeast, 3/4 cup white flour, 3/4 cup whole wheat flour and baking soda.
Add cooled liquid mixture to yeast flour mixture and then add egg, spices and grated onion.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.

title: fesmire's chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and place in 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish. Spread preserves on chicken.
Sprinkle the dried soup over the chicken.
Then pour dressing to cover dish.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 375°.
Sometimes I uncover the dish the last 5 to 10 minutes in oven.
Serve over rice.

title: caramel crunch apple pie
directions: Melt caramels with water in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Spoon apples into crust; top with caramel sauce.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts; sprinkle over apples.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: mexican wedding or tea cakes
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugar in electric mixer. Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of large marbles.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Cool, then roll again.

title: sauerkraut and kielbasi
directions: Rinse sauerkraut in colander about 2 to 3 times well; drain. In large skillet with lid, saute onion with butter until yellow. Add sauerkraut and 1/2 cup water.
On medium-low flame, semi-cover pan and cook until sauerkraut becomes limp and golden, stirring occasionally, about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Do not burn.
(Water will evaporate.)

title: miniature peanut butter cups
directions: Melt chocolate bar and 1/2 cup peanut butter in saucepan.
In separate pan, melt peanut butter (1 cup).
In lined candy cup pan, layer chocolate and peanut butter mixture.
Cool, then add layer of melted peanut butter.
Cool, then add top layer of chocolate peanut butter mixture.
Cool.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Set aside.
Heat the brown sugar, molasses, water, seeds, Crisco and rind to boiling.
Pour over 5 cups rye flour.
When lukewarm, mix two mixtures together well and add unbleached flour until at the kneading stage.
Knead well.
Let rise and form into 5 large or 8 smaller loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar free cherry cake
directions: Bring pineapple with juice to a boil.
Meanwhile, drain cherries, reserving juice.
Add both boxes of gelatin and cherry juice to pineapple.
Let cool slightly.
Stir in cherries, cola, and Equal.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Boil the cabbage in the water with the salt.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Add milk, vinegar and sugar, then add the well beaten eggs.
(Add the eggs very slowly, stirring rapidly to prevent their cooking on contact.)
Add celery salt and pepper. Continue heating until eggs are thoroughly cooked, stirring constantly.

title: spinach, mushroom and red onion salad
directions: Marinate mushrooms in combined lemon juice and oil.
Toss with onion, spinach and greens, then season with vegetable seasoning and kelp.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Reserve.
Melt butter and chocolate; remove from heat and let cool.
Add granulated sugar and eggs, mixing thoroughly after each egg.
Beat for 1 or more minutes.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Remove dough from bowl, scraping sides with a spatula.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, preferably overnight.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Place balls 3 inches apart and bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until tops are set.
Cool on wire racks.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Mix marshmallows, milk and Hershey bars over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool mixture, then add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil for 9 to 10 minutes to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm, about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture begins to lose its gloss and hold shape (very little beating required). Quickly stir in nuts.
Turn into a well-greased pan and let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: salmon asparagus pie
directions: Thaw and drain asparagus if frozen.
Grease 10-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Put into pie plate in order: asparagus, onion, 3/4 of cheese and fish.

title: quick mulled cider
directions: Combine apple cider and mulling spices in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain cider and serve.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Add chocolate.
Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened.
Continue to cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir at least half of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Stir egg yolk mixture into mixture in saucepan.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer. Remove from heat and blend vanilla
into batter. Cool 20 minutes and beat approximately 30 seconds until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add remaining sugar, slowly, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over filling, carefully sealing to crust. Bake in hot 425° oven for 6 minutes or until browned.
Cool about 4 hours.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan; heat until mixture bubbles, stirring occasionally, to prevent sticking. Serves 5.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend sugars, salt and milk in boiler.
Cook over medium heat. When it starts boiling, cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook to soft ball stage.

title: carrot spice cake
directions: Place carrots, sugar, water, raisins, butter and spices in a saucepan.
Bring to a boiling point and cook slowly for 5 minutes. Place pan over ice cubes to cool mixture quickly.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add with nuts to first mixture and mix quickly and thoroughly.
Place in a well-greased floured tube pan.
Bake in oven at 350° to 375° for 50 minutes or more, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and margarine.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in bowl; fold and mix well.
Spoon into pastry-lined pie plate and top with remaining pastry dough.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn temperature down to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: walnut drop cookies
directions: Roll and put in refrigerator until cold, then slice thin and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: 10 minute tomato soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring tomatoes to a boil.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Return to heat; cook until butter melts and soup is heated through.
Yields 3 to 4 bowls.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast 1 cup coconut for 5 to 7 minutes. Reserve 1/2 cup for frosting.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. In large bowl, blend cake mix, water, 1/2 cup pineapple juice, oil, rum and egg whites at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir in 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil for about 2 minutes.
Set aside.
While hot, stir in the peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop onto wax paper or a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: cucumber crisp
directions: Peel and cube cucumbers.
Add to water and lime mixture (use crock or plastic container) that the lime has been dissolved in overnight.
Wash cucumbers under running water until water is clear.
Put cucumbers in ice water for 2 hours.
Drain cucumbers. Mix vinegar, sugar and spices.
Add cucumbers; let set overnight.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Mix in crock-pot bowl.
Start
on
high for 30 minutes, then cut temperature down to low and let it go!

title: hunsmickel pie(spelled phonetically)
directions: Mix approximately 1/4 cup milk with flour and blend in sugar; sweeten to taste.
Add dash of cinnamon and pour into pie shell. Add dab of butter in the center.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes with your large pie on a separate shelf.
It bakes best on an upper rack.

title: mccormick chicken
directions: Mix mayo, milk and chicken soup.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish half of this mixture, chicken cutlets, then rest of mixture.
Take bread and put in blender to make bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Mix with sugar and shortening mixture.
Stir in pecans and refrigerate overnight.

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pan.
Whisk together flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Stir in oatmeal. Beat together butter, sugar milk and egg in a bowl.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until evenly moistened.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour in muffin pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: dump salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese and mix.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Add pineapple and mix.
Refrigerate until set.
Best to make day before.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix and let stand for several hours before using.

title: fried ice cream
directions: With scoop, form 6 ice cream balls. Place on waxed paper lined tray. Cover and freeze several hours or until firm.
In medium mixing bowl, combine vanilla wafer crumbs and coconut.
Set aside. In a small mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Coat ice cream balls with crumb mixture, pressing firmly into ice cream.
Dip balls in beaten eggs.
Coat again with crumb mixture.
Place on waxed paper lined tray. Freeze for 2 hours or until very firm.
Just before serving, heat 2-inches of oil in frying pan or deep fryer to 375°. Remove 2 balls at a time from freezer.
Fry in hot fat 20 to 25 seconds or until browned. Drain. Serve immediately with honey or chocolate sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat together eggs, granulated sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Mix together cinnamon, salt, soda, flour and baking powder.
Stir into mixture.
Add pumpkin to mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in an ungreased pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and brown.
Add onion and saute.
Mix rest of ingredients and add bacon, onion and 1/2 cup bacon grease (optional).
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 325°.
Serves 20.

title: four layer torte
directions: Cream 1 cube margarine with 1 cup flour and chopped pecans. Pat into a 10 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cool!
Stir cream cheese with 1 cup Cool Whip folded in with
1 cup powdered sugar.
Spread mixture over baked layer.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: pineapple lemon mousse jello
directions: Heat juice to boiling.
Stir in gelatin and stir until dissolved, about 1 minute.
Stir in yogurt.
Chill until thickened slightly. Stir in pineapple sauce.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Put corn, Ro-Tel, taco mix and cheese in pan and cook to melt cheese. Mix rice with cheese mixture, then add meat and onions. Mix well and put in slow cooker to keep hot to serve.

title: beg for more garlic rolls
directions: Separate biscuit dough and tear each in half.
Roll like a snake and tie into knot.
Bake per package directions until lightly brown.
Remove from oven; place in a large bowl.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice in saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups; bring to boil.
Add to jello.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Whip cream. Add sugar.
Fold into jello mixture.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend well.
Chill 3 hours.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise; stew a few minutes.
Place on baking sheet.
Put butter over them.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: orange jello
directions: Combine the jello and the boiling water, following the package directions.
Allow the jello to gel slightly.
Add the fruit, orange sherbet and Dream Whip.
Put into a jello mold and refrigerate until set.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine pineapple and Jell-O in a saucepan over low heat until Jell-O dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, baby food and cream cheese.
Stir, but do not beat.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into an 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice thin. Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves. Add salt and cover with cracked ice. Mix well. Let set 3 hours. Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture. Heat just to a boil. Seal in hot sterilized jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: quick biscuits
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, wheat germ and baking powder; add milk and yogurt.
Stir together until combined.
Allow batter to set for 5 minutes.

title: sure pie crust
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening until pea size.
Combine egg yolk, vinegar and water. Add liquid mixture to dough.

title: kick the can ice cream
directions: Pour milk in 1 pound coffee can and add soda to about 1-inch from top.
Put on lid and seal with duct tape.
Place can in larger coffee can.
Surround with ice.
Put on lid and seal.
Let children roll the can on the ground (gently) for at least 20 minutes or until ice cream becomes firm.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter parfait
directions: Combine flour, chopped peanuts and oleo.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese, peanut butter, powdered sugar and whipped topping.
Place over cooled crust.
Chill.
Combine chocolate and vanilla pudding with milk.
Beat until thick.
Pour over 2nd chilled layer. Chill.
Top with additional whipped topping.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Chill until set.

title: corvina native style(from ecuador)
directions: Slice and cook tomatoes, onion, green pepper, parsley and sugar in a little oil, making a "refrito".
Mix corvina with the refrito.
Add potatoes, cut into cubes.
Add white wine and water if necessary.
Cover and cook slowly until done (about 15 or 20 minutes).
To serve, decorate with wedges of tomatoes and hard-boiled eggs and raisins.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly. Stir in water. Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Heat oven to 400°.

Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 7 to 8 minutes until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly with finger. While slightly warm frost with Quick Cream Icing.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemony cheese cake squares
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, sugar and margarine; mix well. Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: mom ever's chocolate cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs and butter.
Add cocoa mixture, buttermilk, soda, vanilla, flour and salt.
Spread in two round cake pans lined and floured.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Frost with Waldorf Frosting.

title: meat balls in quick mushroom sauce
directions: To one can condensed mushroom soup, add 2/3 cup milk and 2 teaspoons grated onion.
Heat and pour over warm meat balls.
Place in a chafing dish and use as an hors d'oeuvres.
As a main entree, serve over a bed of buttered noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken chili casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Pour crushed chips in bottom.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chips.
Top with grated cheese and heat in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, drain and pour into casserole dish.
Over top, in layers put soup, Velveeta and bread.
On top, pour melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water; drain well.
Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients into egg mixture and beat well.
Add coconut to dough. Pour into 7 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread marshmallow cream over top. Frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: baked custard
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and salt together in a small mixing bowl. Slowly stir in milk.
Add flavoring. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° in large baking pan of hot water, 45 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
(Drizzle honey over top (optional). Serve warm or chilled.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rhubarb conserve
directions: Place rhubarb in a large saucepan.
Cut each orange slice into 8 pie-shaped wedges, and each lemon slice into 14 pie-shaped wedges.
Add to the rhubarb along with sugar, and mix well.
Bring to a boil over high heat, then lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes longer.
Label into sterilized jars and process in a water-bath canner at a simmering temperature of 180° to 185° for 10 to 15 minutes.
This conserve also freezes very well.
Serve on crackers, toast or bagels, with or without cream cheese.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Makes sheet cake or layer cake.
Add any frosting or hot fudge.

title: pepperoni spaghetti
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, beef and pepperoni in a large skillet. Cook over medium heat until beef browns, stirring to crumble. Remove from heat and drain. Return beef mixture to skillet. Add sauce and bring to a boil; cover. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain. Arrange in pan and spoon meat sauce on top. Sprinkle cheese over sauce. Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove and top with Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and remove from pan.
In same pan, fry macaroni and onion until golden brown.
Add hamburger and rest of ingredients.
Cook on low heat until done, about 40 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and cook slowly over moderate heat, stirring often. Cook until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and add rest of the ingredients. Boil about 1 minute or until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute margarine and onions until tender (limp).
Layer onions, cheese and crackers.
Make at least 2 layers of all ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: crystal pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening; gradually add and continue to cream sugar with shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: snappy cheese apple
directions: Combine all ingredients except chili powder, cinnamon and bay leaf.
Form into shape of an apple. Sprinkle generously with chili powder.
Make stem with stick of cinnamon and add bay leaf. Chill.
Slice and serve with assorted crackers.
Or, shape into rolls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter before rolling in chili powder.
Chill.

title: praline cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with sheet of greased foil.
Break apart graham crackers into single pieces.
Place side-by-side on cookie sheet.
Melt oleo; add brown sugar.
As mixture begins to boil, add nuts.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°. Let cool, then break apart.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain fat.
Separate rolls and press into 12-inch pizza pan (points to center).
Spoon sausage, potatoes and cheese on top.
In bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick baked onion potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake together oil, onion soup mix and cubed potatoes in Ziploc bag or bowl with lid until potatoes are covered evenly.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef in butter.
Add onion and celery.
Add cooked noodles, drained.
Add cream soups and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle slivered almonds and paprika on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: turnip gratinee
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rub a small gratin dish with garlic clove, then butter it well.
Parboil the turnips for 2 to 3 minutes and drain.

Arrange 1/3 of the turnip slices in a layer in the dish. Sprinkle them with salt and pepper and half the herbs. Mix the 2 cheeses and sprinkle the turnips with 1/3 of the mixture. Repeat layers, finishing with the cheese on top.
Pour cream over the dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy glazed carrots
directions: Cover carrots with salted boiling water in a skillet.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain carrots and return them to the skillet.
Add butter, sugar and vermouth.
Cook uncovered for 5 minutes or until wine has evaporated and carrots are glazed and shiny.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and milk and beat.
Stir in chopped rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes or more.
Inserted knife should come out clean.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish and cover with chicken (torn apart in bite size pieces).
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
(Ritz crackers are good.)
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lou's spinach salad
directions: Cut or tear spinach coarsely into salad bowl.
Cook diced bacon in a skillet over moderately high heat until crisp.
Reduce heat to moderate; add sugar, onions, salt, vinegar, mustard and paprika.
Bring to the boiling point and remove from heat.
Just before serving, pour the hot dressing over the spinach and toss lightly until leaves are coated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by tablespoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until not gooey in the middle.

title: ding bats
directions: Combine dates, shortening, sugar and egg.
Cook in double boiler for 15 minutes and then pour over Rice Krispies and nuts. Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Place on waxed paper to set.

title: almond joy
directions: Mix first ingredients; form into balls.
Chill.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meats, crumbs, pepper, eggs and milk. Mix thoroughly. Form in loaf in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. Serve with horseradish sauce. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine sweet potatoes, margarine, sugar, vanilla, eggs and nutmeg. Mix well. Pour into unbaked deep dish pie crust. Bake for 10 minutes at 400 degrees. Reduce temperature to 350 degrees. Continue baking for an additional 35 minutes or until a thin knife blade comes out clean when inserted into center of the custard. Cool completely before slicing.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Make meat sauce.
Stir in drained spaghetti.
Place 1/2 spaghetti-meat sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake casserole at 375° for 30 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and cook 1 hour on low heat.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Heat until warm the soups, broth and salsa. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chicken sauce, tortillas, onion and cheese layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, except for the last 5 minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee(a-too-fay)
directions: Make a shallow cut down shrimp; wash out vein.
Heat butter in medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour; cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in onions, green peppers, celery and garlic.
Cook until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until shrimp are pink.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Cream together sugar and 2 teaspoons oleo.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour batter into baking dish on which 1 teaspoon oleo has been melted.
Pour peaches or cherries.
Bake at 375° until batter is done.
Done is when a toothpick is stuck in and brought out clean.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and 1/2 onion (chopped) until tender.
Drain off water and add 1/2 stick oleo.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk to make soup consistency and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Mix well the pumpkin pie mix and eggs.
Add evaporated milk and blend.
Spread this mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch buttered pan. Sift the cake mix over the mixture.
Dribble margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Can add dollop of Cool Whip but it is delicious served plain.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add milk; mix again until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; mix again.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Eat pie while frozen.

title: cheese batter bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in broth. Add butter, sugar, salt, poultry seasoning, egg and 1 cup flour, beat until smooth, about 1 minute. Add 1 cup cheese and the remaining flour, stir for 1 minute. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes. Stir the batter about 25 strokes. Spread evenly into a greased 9x5x3-inch loaf pan. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 20 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onion salt if desired. Bake at 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from the pan and serve warm.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter in a pot.
Put potatoes in the pot and fill with water.
Bring to a boil.
Add corn and creamed corn and 2 cans full of milk or heavy cream (1 of each).
Add salt and pepper and butter.
Turn heat to medium and simmer until potatoes are soft.
Enjoy!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cheese and mayonnaise; blend until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream, fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into 1-quart container.
Freeze until firm.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots with a little butter.
Add the broth; boil.
Add the cauliflower; cook until tender.
Add milk and heat.
Thicken with a paste made with 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons flour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato clam soup
directions: In saucepan, cook the bacon until almost crisp. Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in flour, salt, savory, thyme and pepper. Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Set clams aside.
Blend in reserved clam liquid and 1 cup water to saucepan ingredients.
Add potatoes.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in clams, milk and parsley.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, but egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into other mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Cook until knife comes out clean.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoonfuls into 2 to 4 tablespoons melted butter or margarine.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side, until lightly browned.

title: simple bean soup
directions: Saute onions. Mix and dilute soup with water. Mix all. Simmer until potatoes are cooked. Season with salt and pepper.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rice with onion soup.
Place chicken legs in pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with milk and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: basic fruit punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot tea. Mix together with juices.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and scatter mint leaves on top. Serve over ice.

title: blueberry cupcakes
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in the egg. In another bowl, sift together the flour, powder, soda and spices. Stir into the creamed mixture alternately with the milk, just until mixed.
Fold in the blueberries.
Fill 12 muffin cups that have been lined with paper (or lightly greased); fill each 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° until golden, about 20 minutes.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Good the first day, even better the second.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in sheet pan
or 2 layers.

title: condensed milk
directions: Place warm water in a bowl.
Add dry milk; mix well.
Add sugar; mix until smooth.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: yankee best ever juicy turkey
directions: In roaster (to fit bird) put clean and seasoned turkey.
(Rub with butter and seasonings.)
Add onions, cleaned and cut into wedges.
Pour broth over all.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Reduce heat to 300° and cook 15 minutes per pound of meat, usually about 1 to 1 1/2 hours (no basting).

title: bean salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and combine vegetables and cheese.
Just before serving, add Fritos and dressing and toss.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion until transparent.
Add rice and hot broth.
Bring to a boil on top of range.
Cover and place in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve and listen to compliments.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gourmet casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet using medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Continue cooking until vegetables are limp.
Drain off excess fat.
Add uncooked rice, cheese, both soups, mushrooms and pimientos.
Mix well.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover; bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: butter morsel cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs and oleo.
Spread in 9 x 15-inch cake pan or jelly roll pan for thicker cake.
Then mix together the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: swiss mocha coffee mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in airtight container.

title: easy cheesy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Combine ingredients. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together.
Fold in 1/4 bag mini chocolate chips.
Pour into graham cracker crust or Oreo cookie crust.
Put in freezer. Serve frozen.

title: broccoli-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
Cook frozen broccoli per package directions.
Cook soup, mixing with 1 1/2 cans water or milk until smooth.
Layer as follows in casserole dish:
noodles, broccoli, soup and cover with cheese.
Repeat, then cook 30 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: surprise bacon
directions: Cut bacon in 3 pieces and prunes in half.
Roll and put a toothpick in each roll.
Broil until bacon is crisp.

title: emancipation proclamation breakfast cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch Pyrex plate.
Combine butter flavor Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Pat dough out to 1/2-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut into nine 3-inch rounds.
Place one in center of Pyrex plate.
Arrange eight, tilted and overlapping, around center dough circle.
Spread with honey. Sprinkle with orange and lemon peel.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 24 minutes or until dough in center is thoroughly baked.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: medley salad
directions: Chop all ingredients into small pieces. Mix together the vegetables. Pour the dressing over them and marinate overnight.

title: pam spread
directions: Whip
until fluffy.
Store at room temperature.
Use on cake, corn bread pans, etc., to keep from sticking.

title: party dip
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve with Doritos.

title: chicken andouille gumbo
directions: Brown chicken in 1/2 cup oil.
In a pot, make a roux with oil and flour; cook until golden brown.
Put chicken back in pot; simmer in roux after adding all seasonings and liquids.
Cook over medium heat for about 2 1/2 hours.
Add water, if needed, to retain volume.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs, soup, mayonnaise, pimentos, lemon juice, onion, salt and Accent.
Place in a large greased rectangular baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Next cheese, then almonds.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves eight.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir into cabbage.

title: antipasto
directions: Heat butter in skillet; add anchovies, mushrooms and garlic. Saute and add wine and 1 tablespoon of lemon juice.
Increase heat and cook 5 minutes.
Season with pepper.
Cool to almost room temperature and add cheese, salami, onion, capers and parsley. Add remaining lemon juice, olive oil and vinegar; toss well. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature as appetizer. Makes 2 cups.

title: strawberry heavenlow calorie delight
directions: Add strawberries to jello and pour into the crust, let it stand for 30 minutes. Make the pudding while jello is setting. Pour over jello layer, let it stand for another 30 minutes, until set. Spread "La Creme" on top and decorate with slivered almonds.

title: swiss venison steak
directions: Dredge steaks in flour and season with salt and pepper.
Pound into meat.
Brown meat quickly in butter and set aside.
Saute onions in pan until soft.
Return meat to pan, covering it with onions and then tomatoes.
Add herbs and wine.
Cover and simmer slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning meat once or twice.
If gravy becomes too thick, add a little more wine.

title: super baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish or bean pot.
Strip the top with bacon.
Bake at 350° until the bacon is done and the beans are hot.

title: millionaire # cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter. Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each one. Alternate flour and milk, beating well. Add vanilla.
Pour in greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: christmas suet pudding
directions: Place ingredients in a clean white cloth and tie.
Set in bowl in water and steam for 3 hours or pressure cooker for 40 minutes. Serve with white sauce.

title: green beans with new potatoes
directions: Break string beans in pieces to cook.
In large cooking pan put clean washed green beans, water about 2 inches over beans with salt and oil or bacon fat.
Cook to boiling for 10 minutes. Turn heat to medium-low for 1 hour.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Saute the onion in a tablespoon of butter. When partially cooked, add mushrooms and rice. Continue to saute. Add beef broth. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Keep in airtight container.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken with dressing.
Coat with combined ingredients. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
together and set aside.	Combine water, vanilla, oil and vinegar.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake
at
for
25 to 30 minutes. Makes 2 (9-inch) round
layers,
a
9 x 13-inch sheet cake or 30 cupcakes.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cut in squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grilled dove breast
directions: Filet dove breast from breast bone.
Quarter jalapeno peppers lengthwise and remove seeds; quarter onion and separate skins.
Put one quarter jalapeno pepper, one piece of onion and a healthy dash of creole seasoning between two pieces of filet held together with 1/2 slice of bacon and a toothpick.
Repeat this process for each dove.
Place in flat dish.
Mix salad dressing and Worcestershire sauce and pour over top; let marinate for 10 minutes or more.
Cook over hot charcoal fire for 10 to 12 minutes, depending on temperature of the fire.
You want the bacon to be crisp.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can be refrigerated or frozen.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter, then add soup; mix. Add cream cheese and heat until melted. In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread frozen hash browns. Pour hot cheese mixture on top and spread to cover potatoes. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Top with Cheddar cheese the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: cinnamon bubble bread
directions: Preparation Time:
40 minutes. Rising Time:
About 2 hours. Oven Temperature:
Baking Time:
Loaf, 30 minutes; rolls, 20 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and break into large pieces.
Cook broccoli slightly.
Put all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bacon wrap ups
directions: Wrap bacon around crackers.
Place as many as will fit on a broiler pan.
Cook at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes to an hour. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over each cracker; drain.
Great for company snacks.

title: cookies from any cake mix
directions: Mix. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: italian cream cake and frosting
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Mix flour and soda; add to mixture.
Add buttermilk; stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans and fold in egg whites.
Pour in tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 1 large loaf or 3 small loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Beat in pumpkin, oil or applesauce and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Fold in walnuts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl, then mix next 3 ingredients in another bowl.
Then add egg and vanilla and mix all together in one bowl.
Roll into small balls and place on a greased cookie sheet, then cross press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: pineapple apricot salad
directions: Drain pineapple and apricots; reserve 1 cup juice from each. Dissolve orange Jell-O in boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup each pineapple and apricot juice.
When cool, add pineapple and apricots and marshmallows.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch dish.
Jell until firm.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 8 to 10 biscuits.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix.
Add mincemeat with soda dissolved in it.
Nuts may be added.
Drop by teaspoons and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: aristocratic slices
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Mix slices and onions together. Cover with salt water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Wash in clear water 3 times.
Drain well.
Add sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Cook all in large container for 20 minutes.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: butterscotch-peanut krispies(microwave)
directions: In large microwave-safe glass bowl, combine margarine and butterscotch chips.
Microwave on High until melted, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Add marshmallows.
Microwave on High until melted, about 2 minutes.
Stir in Rice Krispies and peanuts. Press, by hand sprayed with Pam, into 8 x 12-inch glass dish. Cool and cut into squares.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown onion in Wesson oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper 8 chicken breasts and place in a 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with tin foil.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: sugar-free zesty popcorn munch
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a bowl; drizzle with melted margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to popcorn mixture. Toss well.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides).

title: sauteed carrots and zucchini
directions: Saute carrot and onion in skillet for 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and salt.
Saute for 3 minutes or until zucchini is tender or crisp.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar, add eggs.
Make paste of cocoa and red color.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Sift flour and salt together then with mixer at medium speed, add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend well; add vanilla.
Combine vinegar and soda and while still foaming add to batter.
Do not beat, add gently.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch layers.

title: minced clam spaghetti
directions: Saute garlic and onions in olive oil and butter on low heat until just colored.
Add the clam juice (about 1/2 cup); simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in minced clams and parsley; bring to a boil.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Saute onions until transparent.
Add ground beef and green pepper; cook until browned.
Add all the remaining ingredients and mix together.
Turn the mixture into a casserole dish and bake it for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and re-sift with sugar and salt.
In a saucepan put margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over the flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl, put eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to the other mixture and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured shallow cake pan (cookie sheet with at least one inch sides).
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Start the icing the last 5 minutes the cake is baking.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add oil and buttermilk; mix thoroughly.
Add dissolved yeast to this mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Pinch off amount needed.
Knead with dry flour.
Bake in greased pan at 450°.
Store rest in refrigerator.
Will last about a week.

title: acapulco delight
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Add salsa and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan, line with 1 to 1 1/2 tortillas and spread half of meat mixture, then 1/4 cup cheese on top of meat.
Top with another tortilla.
Spread refried beans and cover with 2/3 of sour cream. Sprinkle with green onions and olives.
Cover with 1 more tortilla. Layer meat and cheese on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomato and remaining sour cream.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream the
butter
and	sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and
beat well. Add flour and cream alternately, a small amount at a time.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast and stir well.
Add eggs, then flour.
Mix to a smooth, soft dough.
Knead lightly on a floured surface.
Place dough in a greased bowl; cover with a wet cloth and let rise until at least doubled in bulk.
Divide dough in thirds.
Roll each third on lightly floured surface to a 10-inch circle.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut each circle into 8 to 12 wedge-shaped pieces.
Roll each wedge, starting with the wide end and rolling to the point. Arrange on a greased baking sheet and brush with melted butter. Cover and let rise until light.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 minutes or less.
If desired, brush with a brown sugar and water glaze.

title: st. louis gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan the cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs. Pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: red macaroni
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in a large, heavy pan.
Drain off all fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, water or juice, garlic powder, sugar, salt and pepper; stir well.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: minnesota cucumbers
directions: Combine vegetables; stir sugar to dissolve in vinegar.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Cover and store in refrigerator. (If doubling the amount of the recipe, reduce the amount of celery seed.)
It is ready to eat after being in the refrigerator overnight.
It keeps about 2 weeks.

title: christmas rock cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add soda dissolved in hot water.
In another large bowl mix raisins, flour, nuts, candied cherries, spices and salt.
Add butter mixture to all this.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
It was so thick I had to form it into a small ball with my hand.
Bake at 350° about 8 minutes or until brown.
Will make about 8 dozen.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add bouillon cube and mushrooms with juice.
Skin chicken and drain.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of sauce on 1 slice turkey ham, then add 1 slice of cheese, 1 chicken breast and roll.
Hold with a toothpick.
Make all six.
Place in a greased dish, seam side down.
Pour white sauce over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: heavenly shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add to heated soup and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into oiled mold.
Serve well chilled.

title: maple cake
directions: Mix with spoon.
Bake in 15 x 7 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes at 325°.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil thoroughly.
Add flour, flavoring and mix well.
Add pecans.
Lightly grease pan.
Do not leave in oven any longer than 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, corn oil and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, 1 teaspoon salt and allspice.
Add to mixture.
Pour into greased cake pans and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook vegetables and drain.
Mix soup and milk.
Add cheese and mix together.
Add chicken, vegetables and noodles.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs. Melt margarine and pour on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down
directions: Grease oblong dish.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of dish.
Prepare mix by directions.
Pour batter over nuts and coconut.
Set aside.
Prepare icing of cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
