Most icing will sink to bottom of cake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: moo burgers
directions: Thoroughly combine first 5 ingredients.
Crush corn flakes slightly with hands.
Gently stir into meat mixture.
Let stand 1/2 hour.

title: pizza buttons
directions: Twist off mushroom stems.
Trim inside mushroom to enlarge cavity.
Saute in butter the garlic, onion, zucchini and basil. Remove from heat; blend in tomato sauce.
Stuff pepperoni into bottom of mushroom.
Add mix; sprinkle with cheese.
Line pan with parchment paper.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: southern spoonbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Gradually stir about one-fourth of the hot mixture into eggs; add to the remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Add flour with baking powder and salt.
Alternate mixture with 1 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: reuben pie
directions: Blend together the egg, milk, bread crumbs, onions, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add sauerkraut, ground beef and corned beef; mix well.
Place half of meat mixture into shell; sprinkle half the cheese on top.
Add rest of the meat mix and cheese to pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes, or until crust is browned.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together and press in ungreased pan.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornbread mix.
Add it and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 450°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the zucchini. Fold in nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Puree
garlic and onion together.
Add all other ingredients; blend.
Yields 1 quart.

title: chicken breast burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
While keeping hands moist with warm water, form small patties.
Saute over medium heat in a skillet with corn oil.

title: sausage kebob
directions: Chunk onion, pepper and sausage. Alternate ingredients, including tomatoes, on skewer and cook for 35-45 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Simmer on high for 1 hour, then simmer on low for 2 to 4 hours.

title: tasty casserole
directions: Put green beans in bottom of pan.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream, onion and water chestnuts. Pour over green beans.
Pour creamed corn on
top. Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Great for diabetics.

title: shrimp scampi and pasta
directions: Boil water in large pot for pasta.
Combine broth, garlic and 3 tablespoons each of shallots and parsley in large saucepan.
Bring slowly to a simmer, cook 2 minutes.
Add pasta to boiling water and cook according to directions.
Add shrimp to broth, stir well and cook for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until shrimp are cooked through. Add remaining shallots.
Drain pasta; divide evenly among large shallow plates.
Arrange shrimp over pasta and spoon broth sauce over shrimp.
Sprinkle with pepper; garnish with remaining parsley. Serve immediately.
Serves 6 as an appetizer or 4 as an entree.

title: baked beef and noodles
directions: Cook 1 small bag of egg noodles.
Set aside.
Saute onion and ground beef.
Season to taste.
Combine all ingredients.
Put into a 2-quart baking dish, top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: cajun party mix
directions: Combine cereals, pretzels and nuts and pour onto ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch sheets.
Mix butter and seasonings and pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 40 to 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 8 cups.

title: bean and bacon soup
directions: Combine beans and water in large kettle.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour, then boil again until tender.
Fry
bacon
until crisp, then cook onions in bacon fat.
Add
to
soup
with
bacon drippings.
Also add tomato juice, then simmer 1 hour.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Pressure can
hours or cold pack 3 hours.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs and add molasses.
Add combined and sifted dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and cheese. Put in casserole dish.
Mix together grated crackers and cheese. Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Heat at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Mix together and lay in bottom of pan.

title: dinosaur dip
directions: Mix all together well and chill.
Serve with fresh veggies (broccoli, carrot sticks, celery sticks, cauliflower, radishes and onions).

title: salad
directions: Put almonds in heavy pan with 2 tablespoons sugar over medium-high heat to coat.
Separate.
Toss first 5 ingredients together.
Just before serving, add almonds and dressing of vinegar, sugar and oil.

title: levi's bird
directions: Put
chicken
in
12-inch
Dutch oven.	Pour water over chicken.
Pour
mushrooms, onion soup mix, margarine, salt and pepper over
chicken.
Bake with 6 coals on top and 5 coals on the bottom
for
hours.
Replenish	coals
1/2 way through cooking process or as needed to maintain even temperature

title: two step pistachio salad
directions: Pour all ingredients in a large bowl and stir.
Wait for pudding to set and enjoy!
Serve chilled.

title: carrot and pineapple slaw
directions: Blend together mayonnaise or salad dressing, sour cream, onion, lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Combine pineapple, carrots, cabbage and almonds in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise mixture; toss well.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla extract, butter flavor, pineapple and 1 cup bananas.
Spoon batter into three 9-inch round greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Spread with frosting and sprinkle the chopped pecans on top.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Butterfly flank steak.
Be careful not to cut into two separate pieces.
Open flank steak and rub with garlic.
Spread cream cheese over meat.
Place spinach leaves on cream cheese.
Sprinkle pimentos and mushrooms over spinach.
Lay dried beef over steak. Season with fresh ground black pepper.
Carefully roll flank steak and secure edge with toothpicks.
Place in dish and pour beef broth and wine over rolled steak.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar together.
Spread each slice of bread with cream cheese mixture.
Roll up and cut in half or thirds.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Dip rolls into butter and place on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: *bran oatmeal muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over bran and set aside while mixing the rest of the ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, buttermilk, salt, flour and soda.
Add oatmeal last.
Use some of mix, if desired, and refrigerate remainder.

title: date and apricot bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
In another bowl, beat eggs until light.
Add milk and oil.
Stir into flour mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove to rack and cool completely.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix all together and form cookie balls.
Press each down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add pineapple juice and water to equal 1 cup.
Cook until thickened and cool.
Add to mixture the pineapple, oranges, bananas and maraschino cherries.

title: escabeche or redfish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and let rest 30 minutes.
Drain and pat each piece dry.
Saute scallions and garlic in oil.
Add red onions, peppers and bay leaf with fish in batches.
Saute 15 minutes.
Transfer to bowl.
Add lemon and lime juice and reserve.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer evenly in long pan.
Mix 1 small jar Miracle Whip and 1 small container sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread on salad.
Sprinkle with 1 pound fried bacon (crumbled).

title: ham, red beans and rice
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except rice. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Serve over rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocadamia cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, margarine, brown sugar, sugar, egg, water, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until combined, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in chopped chocolate and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto an ungreased large cookie sheet.
Using spatula, flatten each cookie to a 2 1/2-inch round.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown. Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute.
Transfer cookies to wire rack and cool.
Makes 30 to 36 cookies.

title: nacho casserole
directions: In skillet, cook and drain ground beef.
Stir in pork and beans, corn, soup and chili powder or taco seasoning.

Mix well. Turn into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Crush tortilla chips on top and sprinkle on cheese. Return to oven. Bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts, if desired.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over pie and bake 10 minutes.
Top with blueberry or cherry pie filling.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cut butter into 2 cups flour and powdered sugar until like meal.
Put into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and bake about 15 minutes at 30 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Put in lemon juice and rind.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add flour (1/4 cup), coconut and baking powder.
Pour over mixture in pan and cook in 350° oven about 25 minutes.
When cool, cut in bars.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Let set in refrigerator to quivery stage.
Add whipped cream and mayonnaise to gelatin. Blend and add nuts, pineapple, cottage cheese, celery and carrots. Return to refrigerator.
When firmly set, cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Top with dash of mayonnaise, if desired, or as you please.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with 1 tomato paste can of water in small bowl.
Combine ground beef, egg, onion, salt and crackers in large bowl, mixing well.
Add half the tomato paste mixture, mixing well.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Spread remaining tomato paste mixture over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; roll meat in mixture. Brown meat in olive oil (or olive oil/butter). Add onion, garlic and mushrooms. Saut until partially tender. Add liquid, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and green pepper. Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat to simmer. Simmer until meat is tender. Spoon off excess fat (if any). Stir in sour cream. Heat at low temperature; do not boil. Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serve over hot cooked noodles or rice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni for 10 minutes or until done.
Meanwhile, heat oleo and milk together until just warm.
Add cheese, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Add salt.
Pour over drained macaroni. Grate more cheese on top and melt in oven.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add syrup, vanilla and flour.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Use a 4-quart bowl or casserole.
Place the lettuce pieces in bottom of bowl.
Top with the onions, celery, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Spread the mayonnaise evenly over the peas. Sprinkle the sugar, grated Parmesan and garlic salt over the mayonnaise.
Chill 24 hours.
Garnish with the chopped eggs, crumbled bacon and tomato wedges.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add the oleo to the scalded milk and pour over bread crumbs. Add sugar, eggs, nutmeg and raisins.
Pour in a casserole bowl and set bowl in a pan filled 1/4 way up with water.
Put in oven and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This is super!
You'll want to double this recipe!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half mixture in flat mold and chill until almost set.
Spread sour cream evenly over this and add remaining jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Let set.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: peas with tomatoes
directions: Drain liquid from peas into a saucepan.
Cook over high heat until reduced in half.
Add remaining ingredients, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine.
Cook 2 minutes, then serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: homemade graham crackers
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt and add this to creamed mixture along with sweet milk.
This makes a stiff dough.
Roll it out thin and cut into squares.
Prick each with a fork a few times.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until brown.
Watch carefully.

title: brown sugar crumb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, flour and salt.
Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture.
Add buttermilk with soda dissolved in it.
Pour batter into a greased pan.
Sprinkle reserved mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: savory chicken bake
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Combine milk, chicken, chicken soup and savory.
Place layer of broccoli in casserole. Cover with chicken mixture.
Top with broccoli; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, until bubbling, about 20 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings/255 calories per serving.

title: amazing coconut custard pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Blend for three minutes.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peach seafoam salad
directions: Heat peach juice to boiling. Add gelatin. Stir to dissolve. Place gelatin and softened cream cheese into blender container. Blend until smooth. Refrigerate until cool and thick. Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate until thick. Serves 6.

title: broccoli and green olive salad
directions: Bring broccoli to a boil in a small amount of water.
Take off heat, cover and let sit about 5 minutes, so broccoli still remains crisp.
Drain and place in a bowl; add 3/4 cup mayo, 3/4 cup olives, scallions and hard-boiled eggs.
Tastes best when it sits for a few hours before serving.

title: veal in casserole
directions: Trim, pound and season veal.
Brown quickly in very hot frying pan.
Add mushroom soup and water and simmer a few minutes.
Add vegetables; put in casserole and bake for about an hour or until meat is very tender.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Whisk together eggs, cream and butter. Gradually add sugar mixture, whisking until smooth. Stir in corn. Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and set. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: ricotta pie(torta di ricotta)
directions: Sift together into a bowl the flour and salt.
Cut shortening in with pastry blender, until pieces are size of small peas. Sprinkle egg yolks and cold water gradually over mixture, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Mix lightly with fork after each addition. Add only enough water to hold dough together.
Mix until egg is thoroughly combined and completely blended.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Stir in flour, cocoa and salt; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sausage roll
directions: Let your pizza dough rise inside the plastic bag for a few hours!
Cook sausage until tender.
Drain all fat.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add sausage and shredded cheese.
Mix well.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Place 2 teaspoons butter, 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 3 pecan halves in 12 muffin cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat until melted.
Mix applesauce and milk to Bisquick to form dough.
Beat 20 strokes.
Spoon into cups.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Invert on serving dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a medium bowl, sift dry ingredients (first 6).
Beat sugar, pumpkin, oil, eggs and molasses.
Blend in the dry ingredients; mix well.
Add water; fold in raisins (and nuts, optional).
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until center springs back.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove.
Cool to room temperature.

title: mama annie's peanut candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a 3-quart saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
When mixture boils, add butter.
Stir often after it reaches 230° on a candy thermometer.
Add nuts at 280° if raw (add nuts last if roasted).
Stir constantly until mixture reaches 300° or the hard crack stage.
Add baking soda and stir well.
Pour onto two greased cookie sheets and spread to desired thinness.
Loosen candy from cookie sheets as soon as cooled.
Break into pieces.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat sugar and butter until smooth.
Add chocolate chips, melted, and cocoa.
Beat well.
Add 1 egg at
a time, beating well, and vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Refrigerate. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: deviled eggs with ham
directions: Place eggs in 2-quart saucepan.
Cover with water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 12 minutes.
Rinse well with cold water.
Fill pan with more cold water and allow eggs to stand about 30 minutes, until cooled.

title: door county fish boil
directions: Place potatoes and onions in a large kettle with 8 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil and add 1 cup salt.
Boil for 20
minutes. Place fish steaks in a basket and lower into boiling water above the potatoes.
Add another cup of salt and boil for 12 minutes. To test for doneness, the fish should flake easily with a fork and the potatoes should spear easily.
Drain and serve with drawn butter, parsley and lemon.

title: mock curry casserole
directions: Fry sausage until browned.
Remove from skillet and drain off most of the grease.
Brown onion, pepper and celery.
Mix with sausage; add 1 cup rice (not Minute) and noodle soup.
Put in large casserole and cover with chopped almonds or pecans, if desired. When ready to bake, add boiling water and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
You may need to add additional water.

title: sweet and sugar-free topping
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Yields 1/2 cup quick and easy spread on topping.

title: potato cookies
directions: Preheat
oven

Makes 36 cookies.
In a large mixing bowl
combine
butter,
brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; blend at low speed.	Add flour, baking powder and salt;
blend well.
By hand,
stir

potato
flakes
and nuts.	Drop by teaspoonfuls onto
ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10
to
12 minutes
or until lightly browned.	Cool on cookie sheets for 1 minute then remove.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone; crumble crackers and line oblong pan (bottom baking dish) with half of them.
Mix chicken with remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over cracker crumbs.
Place remaining crumbs on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and cook about 5 more minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Spread butter or margarine in pie plate.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Soften the cream cheese and blend in Blue cheese.
Slowly add salad dressing and the light cream.
Add lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Chill.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer the pineapple, blueberries, 3/4 cup sugar sprinkled on blueberries, dry yellow cake mix, melted butter, pecans and 1/4 cup sugar sprinkled on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tex mex bake
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and saute.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper and green chillies.
Mix well.

title: kool-aid shake
directions: In blender, pour 1 cup of milk per serving.
Add 1 heaping tablespoon Kool-Aid per serving and blend.
Pour over 2 scoops of ice cream in iced tea glasses and serve with iced teaspoons.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add butter; mix until smooth.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into two 9-inch glass pie plates that have been greased.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Place diced chillies in bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Layer 2 cheeses on top of chillies.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Beat egg yolks, milk and flour together. Fold in egg whites.
Pour over chillies and cheese layer.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Soften peanut butter and margarine in microwave.
Let cool. Blend in corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Mix until creamy.
Stir in sugar; mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Press in pan.

title: lettuce and onions
directions: Shred lettuce in long slivers, also the onions; toss in bowl. Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Mix a small amount of milk to give the dressing consistency. Pour over lettuce and onions. Delicious with brown beans.

title: spiedies(or a new york shish kabob)
directions: Mix all ingredients, let stand.
Pour over meat and refrigerate overnight to several days.
Put on skewers and can grill or broil.
Great for picnics.

title: creamy peach double decker
directions: Sprinkle peaches with brandy and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water and chill until thickened. Fold peaches into half the gelatin.
Spoon into a 6-cup mold. Chill until set (about 10 minutes).
Blend whipped topping into remaining gelatin.
Put over clear gelatin layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with salad greens.

title: coconut cake and icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Beat about 4 minutes. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat in microwave until cheese is melted and creamy.
Stir frequently.
Makes 2 servings.
Pour over or dip with tortilla chips.

title: dill green tomato pickles
directions: Use small, firm green tomatoes.
Pack into sterilized jars. Add to each quart jar a bud of garlic, 1 stalk of celery and 1 green pepper cut in fourths.
Make a brine of the water, vinegar and salt and boil with the dill for 5 minutes.
Pour the hot brine over the pickles in the jars and seal at once.
These will be ready for use in 4-6 weeks.

title: blueberry-pineapple dessert
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour in blueberry pie filling and pineapple with the juice. Pour the cake mix on top of fruit (dry mix). Melt margarine and pour butter on top of dry cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, salt and eggs; beat until smooth. Add coconut, pecans, raisins and vinegar.
Mix last 4 ingredients by hand.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Put in greased casserole.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise. Spread over vegetables. Melt butter. Combine with crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until nicely browned.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put margarine, salt, syrup and sugar in pan.
Stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Then boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Pour this over popcorn and stir real good.
Put in roasting pan and bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 25 minutes.
Put in Tupperware (air popper is best to use for popcorn).

title: oven denver omelet
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs and cream until light and fluffy.
Stir in the cheese, ham, green pepper and onion.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 4-6.

title: basil tomato salad
directions: Arrange tomatoes, olives and cheese in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake. Pour dressing over tomato mixture, stirring gently.
Cover; chill at least 4 hours.
Serve over red lettuce leaves.

title: pot roast
directions: Put all ingredients in an oven bag; tie and don't peek.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: bacon-cheddar cheese spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat all ingredients together. Serve as a spread on bread or party crackers.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Cool and add sour cream.
Beat with mixer.
Add grated carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in big bowl.
Melt butter in milk in large pot.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Let this come to a rolling boil.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter until melted.
Add oatmeal slowly until mixture is thick.
Spoon balls onto wax paper.
Set until firm.

title: boneless chicken breast
directions: Mix mushroom soup, Minute rice, sour cream and 1/2 package onion soup.
Pour over chicken, then sprinkle the rest of the onion soup on top.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Blend pudding mix, sour cream and milk. Set aside.
In double boiler, melt peanut butter chips and oil, stirring constantly.
Or melt in microwave. Gradually add to pudding, blending well.
Pour into crust. Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with whipped topping.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potatoes pimento
directions: Mix potatoes and pimentos with cream sauce.

title: orange carrots
directions: Combine orange juice, sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in carrots and margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party peas(good and easy)
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add pimientos, water chestnuts and soup and mix well.
Pour mixture over frozen peas in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put into glass gallon jar.
Combine all other ingredients and pour solution over cucumbers.
Sit in a cool place for a week.
Wash cucumbers and slice putting back into jar with 6 cups of sugar and 2 tablespoons water.
Put in refrigerator.
May eat after 2 weeks.

title: marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over meat and let stand overnight to improve flavor.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium-sized bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and
taco seasoning in a separate bowl.
Spread bean dip on a large, shallow
serving
platter;	top
with seasoned avocado mixture. Spread
sour
cream-taco
seasoning mixture over the top. Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives; cover with shredded cheese.
Serve chilled or room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sliced peaches and 1/2 cup sugar together; set aside. Heat oven to 350°.
Put 2/3 stick butter or margarine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and place in oven to melt.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder, flour, salt and milk together.
Pour batter over melted butter; don't stir.
Place peaches over batter; don't stir and bake for 1 hour.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Combine egg, milk and shortening in mixing bowl.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat smooth.
Bake on ungreased griddle.

title: favorite rolls and buns
directions: Dissolve shortening, sugar and salt in scalded milk.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs; beat well.
Then add yeast which has been dissolved in the warm water.
Add to mixture and beat until well mixed.
Then add 2 to 4 cups more flour or enough to make a firm batter.
Knead until smooth.
Put in bowl which has about 2 tablespoons oil.
Turn and put in warm place until double in bulk.
Shape into rolls, cinnamon rolls or loaf.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Slowly melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, milk, corn syrup and vanilla.
Cook slowly.
Dip apples, etc. or top popcorn.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream shortening.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in lemon rind.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Blend in dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven at 325° to 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour glaze made from juice of a lemon and 1/4 cup sugar over cake immediately.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely before slicing.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients
well and chill until serving time. Double for company.

title: no-knead cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, 3 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm by adding water.
Add yeast.
Mix well and let stand 7 minutes.
Blend in egg and flour.
Mix until dough is well blended and smooth.
Roll out dough on floured surface into an 18 x 12-inch shape.

title: pizza treats
directions: Fry sausage lightly; pour off grease.
Add chili powder and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet and bake about 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm.

title: baked ham
directions: Simmer ham together with peppercorns and bay leaves in the cider at 15 minutes per pound.
Remove skin and set aside.
Make diagonal designs on ham and push a whole clove in the middle of each diagonal area.
Combine rest of ingredients in a separate pan and cook for 25 minutes.
Pour this sauce over ham and bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jambalaya(6 servings)
directions: In a stock pot, brown cut up sausage in olive oil.
Remove sausage from pot; saute pepper, onion and garlic in pot for 5 minutes.
Add seasonings and broth; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add rice and sausage; cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes. Add shrimp for last 5 minutes of cooking.
Fluff with fork; cook 5 more minutes.
Serve with Creole sauce.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onions. Put in 9x13 pan. Top with bacon and olives. Bake 1 hour at 325 degrees. Can be mixed early and refrigerated.

title: banana split pie
directions: Line crust with bananas.
Cover with ice cream.
Freeze for two hours.
Remove from freezer and top with fudge sauce. Sprinkle with nuts and top with whipped cream.
Delicious.

title: nutty fudge torte
directions: In a microwave, melt chocolate chips with condensed milk; stir until smooth.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, oil and cinnamon until crumbly.
Set aside 1/2 cup for topping.
In a blender or food processor, process pears until smooth; add to remaining cake mixture with eggs.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 inch spring form pan. Drop melted chocolate by tablespoonfuls over batter.
Combine pecans, water and reserved cake mixture; crumble over chocolate. Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Carefully run a knife around sides of pan to loosen. Cool completely on a wire rack.
Remove sides of pan.
Combine caramel topping and milk until smooth; drizzle on serving plates. Top with a slice of torte.
If desired, serve with whipped cream or ice cream and sprinkle with pecans.
Yield: 12-14 servings.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix unthawed spinach, cheeses, egg, pepper and oregano.
Spread 1/3 cup spaghetti sauce in oblong baking pan.
Place four lasagna noodles over sauce.
Place half of the cheese mixture over noodles. Repeat layer.
Top with remaining lasagna noodles and remaining sauce.
Top with one-half cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour the cup of water around edges of pan.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pecan crunch pie
directions: Mix and beat egg whites and baking powder.
Slowly add sugar and beat until it holds a peak.
Then add the graham crackers. Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Refrigerate for 4 hours before using.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Combine soup, oil, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and hot sauce.
In a 3-quart oblong baking dish or pan, arrange chicken; cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Pour or spoon off fat.
Pour soup mixture over chicken; return to oven for 30 more minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir sauce, then serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date balls
directions: Cook sugar, dates, egg and butter until butter is melted. Cool.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, drain fat.
Put a layer of hamburger in bottom of casserole, then a layer of peas.
Pour chicken soup over hamburger and top with Tater Tots.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Cut the green tops off of onion and chop.
Add cottage cheese and sugar. Mix and serve.

title: fig cake
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients with an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Add orange juice, grated rind and vanilla.
Beat for one more minute.
Blend by hand the sifted flour, soda and salt into first mixture.
Add nuts and fold batter until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured 8 cup Bundt pan Bake at 350° for 50 minutes

title: fudge cake(heavenly and sinful)
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well on medium speed.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each egg is added.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk, mixing well.
Add buttermilk to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips, chocolate syrup, melted German chocolate and vanilla.
Stir until well blended; do not beat.
Spoon batter into heavily greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Turn out immediately onto serving plate; cool completely.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, white sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add milk, Wesson oil and vanilla, mixing only until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into greased shallow baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Mix brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over mixture in baking dish.
Pour boiling water over the top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
When baked, has chocolate sauce on bottom and cake on top.

title: tampa tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea.
Let brew.
Strain.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add ice water and fruit juices.
Pour into 8 tall ice-filled glasses.
If desired, garnish with lime slices and fresh cherries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hazel matthews squash casserole
directions: Slice squash thin.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender, mashing occasionally.
Drain and spread in buttered casserole.
Cover with crushed saltines.
Sprinkle with cheese. Place sliced onion on top.
Beat eggs.
Add soup and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over casserole.
Do not mix with squash and crackers. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
May be cooled and refrigerated, covered.
Just before serving, reheat slowly. Strain to remove spices if desired.
Serve hot in mugs or punch cups with cookies.
Serves 24.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Cook apples and orange juice together until apples are tender; add mincemeat and cook.
Add sugar with flour to mincemeat mixture.
Add 1 cup coconut, pecans and oleo.
This will make two pies.
Bake until crust is brown.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt oleo.
Add Tabasco, Worcestershire and garlic powder. Set oven to 275°.
Let trash get real hot, stirring occasionally. Pour Tabasco mixture over mix.
Stir real good.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: texas ham balls
directions: Blend ham, olives, mustard, Tabasco sauce and onions.
Form into
large balls and chill 15 minutes. Combine cheese and milk. Roll balls into cheese mixture. Chill and remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: In large bowl, put partially frozen lemonade and condensed milk.
Mix until blended, then add Cool Whip.
Stir mixture until well blended.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: black bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, Ro-Tel and spices.
Microwave squash, onion and corn until tender, but crisp (or saute).
Spray dish with Pam. Start with bean mixture, next layer tortillas, then veggies, cheese, then bean mixture and so on.
End with bean mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbly, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mississippi barbecued chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken parts.
Cover with foil and bake for approximately one hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
After baking, while cake is still warm, punch holes in cake with end of wooden spoon every inch.
Pour milk and pina colada over surface of cake. Spread evenly.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Spread pineapple including juice on cake.
Refrigerate until completely cool. Spread Cool Whip and top with coconut.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together first three ingredients.
Bring water, butter and cocoa toa boil; to this add eggs, sour cream and soda. Combine with dry ingredients.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, spray bottom with margarine.
Add 1 cup of hot water.
Add clean, chopped green pepper, onion, garlic, cauliflower, mushrooms and broccoli.
Let the water boil out, then add 1 jar spaghetti sauce and 1 large can chopped tomatoes or sauce.
Stir and simmer on low with cover on pan.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and water.
Add the rest of the ingredients and refrigerate until partly jellied. Fold in Dream Whip. Chill.

title: cocoa crock
directions: Combine cocoa and shortening.
Mash into paste.
Place paste in a container and cover.
Chill until ready to use.
Two tablespoons of the mixture equals 1 ounce or 1 square unsweetened chocolate.

title: frozen 6 salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a pan (Pyrex or plastic) and freeze.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put all chicken pieces in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over and cover chicken pieces.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
